name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
I didn not get to see the whole garden but it was beautiful!
I loved the lakes and amazing flowers all around.

They were celebrating Christmas by planting 100 trees and that was amazing !

There are these beautiful vintage lamps that I just couldn not get over.

It was a Great Walk and the park is detailed with little graphics of information and signage is very helpful.

One of the free attractions of the city!

I recommend going for a picnic and chilling in the gazebos after taking short walks all around :)

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Singapore Botanic Garden is an awesome place for tree lovers and people of all ages. It's a wonderful place for bringing kids and friends. It's also a great place for walking and running. It'll be wise to wear light and white or light colour cloths to seek comfort in humid and high temperature weather. There are a sufficient number of seating arrangements. Along with a large variety of plants, you'll also be able to see turtles, fishes, and birds.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: What a park! Lots of plants are seen their. The attracted things are their that the plants are maintain properly and classified them based on their medicinal properties. Even the name of the specific site is different. It was really a very charming and recommended place. If you have time please go their and enjoy the beauty of nature.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
If you like nature, this place is a must visit. It has an abundance of green spaces, and a ton of different types of landscapes. There are marshes, rolling green fields, forestry and even canals, and more.

It's easy to get to from local train (MRT) stations. The closest two being Napier, and Botanic Garden stations, both of which are a fairly close. Less than ten minutes walk away. There are lots is buses too that stop nearby.

They have clean restrooms, and the staff are helpful.

There's also a really nice waterfall. And a lot of spaces that are great for picnic.

There are sign posts spread frequently throughout the gardens, which makes getting around the (vast) place quite easy.

Best of all... it's free!

All in all, the Botanic Gardens is a fantastic place, easy to get to (thanks to the great transport links), and it gives you access to a ton of serene spaces and nature right in the heart of the city.

Highly recommended ______

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Absolutely fantastic and we couldn't recommend it more highly if you love a garden and wildlife!!! Just the Singapore weather you need to negotiate!  The gardens are huge. We visited for a few hours each on a couple of days! Free entry (but have to pay for the Orchid Gardens if you want to go there), public toilets and also a nice place to eat and lovely gift shop. Ideally situated on Hop on Hop off bus, yellow line too!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Felt really good visiting this place. Very big garden to spend your weekend relaxing. Few people were even camping, a nice picking spot. There are many lakes within. Also don't miss visiting to orchid garden. This one as said is the largest orchid garden in the world. There is a nominal entry fee to orchid garden. Entry to botanical garden is free.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Gorgeous gardens, beautifully kept and maintained. Plenty of path ways throughout. Gardens have many different spaces with a wide variety of plant and tree types, a lot of wildlife scattered around too. Just a shame we couldn't spend longer there. Loved the orchid gardens the most, absolutely massive variety in orchids

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Assumed this would be my least favourite thing to do in Singapore actually turned out to maybe be the best. The gardens are stunning, full of amazing trees, plants and wildlife. We saw turtles, several monitor lizards. Fantastic morning.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
What an amazing place to visit! Very clean, organized and full of energy! So many people bring their dogs for a walk here. The amount of different flowers and trees is remarkable! I fell in love with this place on my first visit
The best thing of all, is that it__ completely free for everyone, and is easily accessible by the MRT. Just brilliant!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A really scenic place. Recommend to come here early mornings so that it would be so hot. Lots of nice views and locations. A really nice museum as well. There's the lake with 2 beautiful swans, a cactus corridor, a small cave with waterfall, orchids, various plants, chicken, the tree that's located on your paper money, the Shaw brothers stage, and a whole lot more

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Singapore Botanic Gardens is a large area with lush green trees. There are several sub-gardens inside it. Orchid Garden is definitely the prime focal attraction among them. It has various types of orchids in the garden. In addition, prominent personalities who visit Singapore and go the Botanic garden as well, specific orchids/flowers are named after them. Its amazing to view and explore this area.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
I came here via train on a late Sunday afternoon in early December 2022. The train station dropped you off at the far north of the garden. Let me tell you - be prepared to get very lost if it's your first time there. This place is huge!

It Is right next to the National University of Singapore. I kept stumbling into the University and having to make my way back into the Garden. There are a lot of people having picnics, taking photos of the birds/plants, exercising,  walking their dogs - you name it! It was 88 degrees Fahrenheit and super humid - I, along with all the dogs I came across, were dying.

I couldn't make it much farther than the Corner House restaurant, which was the main reason I was there since I had reservations. Throughout the garden there were sprinkles of little museums here and there that were open to the public.  They were amazing because they all had air conditioning and restrooms.  If you need something to do to kill time, this is definitely the place to do it. You can easily spend 2 or 3 hours here. Even though the roads are all paved, make sure you bring your comfortable walking shoes.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Nice, large park to walk around or chill in. Lots of trails and different areas, with a couple cafes and shops. In the middle is the national orchid garden which you have to pay to enter. $15 for foreigners, $5 for locals with discounts for seniors and students. Orchid garden had lots of cool areas, and of course lots of very cool and unique orchids.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Enjoyed my time here. Not a lot of people on weekday luckily. Could spot monitor lizards here and there. The park is huge and you have to decide what places you would like to cover. I would recommend going to orchid garden because that gives you access to really cool places one of which looks like Jurassic park location.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Amazing place to picnic, jog and have fresh air. There are many parts in the botanic garden like restaurants, kids garden, live music at the stage in the center of the garden, many entrance to the garden. What I like is the ease from the mrt to access the garden and have many chance to encounter different types of animals like monkeys, monitor lizard, various birds etc. Best to check the weather before going to botanic garden cause there is no rain shelter for most places, so best to have an umbrella for rain and really hot blazing sun.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Singapore Botanic garden is so vast in the area that we could not complete it in one go. It has lots of things to view around like swans, ducklings, foliage garden, children's garden, fragrant garden, healing garden, ginger garden, swan lake, orchid garden, lots of sculptures like flight of swans and a lot more. You can spend the perfect evening with your friends and family here and enjoy being around nature.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: During the Public Holiday visited Botanical Gardens which is a UNESCO sites. A wonderful place and must visit in Singapore. If one a passion for nature to see new trees, flowers, leaves, please visit. There is an Orchid Gardens, which has a nominal entry fee from $3-$15 depends on some categories. It is worth the money. There are 100s of Orchids and many varieties of other flowers. Air plants, mist house and many. Orchid Gardens has great collection, when prominent people from across world like Presidents, Prime Minsters visited Singapore, a new variety which is created will be named after them. There is a huge collection from 1953. Then we walked out and saw a Bonsai tress collection.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: What can I say about Botanic Gardens? It one of our favorite places to visit and we go there quite frequently. It a reasonably large park with a lot to see over a range of different landscapes and themes. You can go there again and again and keep finding something new and engaging. It also a great place for a leisurely walk or a challenging run, as it fairly hilly. It only around 4km in circumference but if you learn the paths through the park itself (the signs can be confusing since the paths tend to twist and turn a lot), you can get in even 15 or 20km with little repetition. In addition to the plants and flowers, there is also a wide variety of wildlife: birds, insects, reptiles, and even otters and monkeys. There are also places to eat, drink, and just take a rest. There is also the National Orchid Garden inside, as well as a variety of museums. If youe never been or if youe been but haven fully explored all the park has to offer, please go and see all that it has to offer. You can even watch the robots go over the lawn at night.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
This is a huge place with many areas suitable for different crowd. You'll find families and couples having picnic, joggers and plenty of beautiful scenery for you to explore and take photos.

We went to the Swan Lake and we were fortunate enough to see one swan floating gracefully on the water. There were many kinds of fishes in the lake as well, and also large terrapins.

On the other side is the large grass patch in front of the amphitheatre where they held various kinds of performances. That is one of the best spots for picnic because of the vast open space for your kids and pets to run around.

Admission is free, carpark fees applies.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Unbelievably good, be prepared to walk for miles as you'll not want to miss one inch of it! Easily got to from the MRT Rapid Transit public transport. DO NOT miss the Orchid Garden is fabulous. All the eateries within the gardens are of great quality.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: This park is huge. A great place to spend an entire day here enjoying the nature and looking at different flora and fauna. Kids like running after the chickens and observing different animals such as the lizards, dragonflies, tadpoles. Remember to bring your insect repellent.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful place to spend time with friends and family. Lovely walk. We visited the orchid park. It has some of the most beautiful orchids in the world in my opinion. Keep a selfie stick handy if you want some lovely pictures with the flowers and greenery

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Gorgeous gardens, beautifully kept and maintained. A really nice museum as well. Plenty of pathways throughout. So many people bring their dogs for a walk here. Gardens have many different spaces with a wide variety of plant and tree types, a lot of wildlife scattered around too. We saw turtles, several monitor lizards. Loved the orchid gardens the most, absolutely massive variety in orchids.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A kid and pet friendly place with places for picnic, open air auditoriums. Wheelchair accessible. Paradise for those who love researching about plants and bird watching. Decent enough places to eat though on the pricier side. It a favourite place for our family to spend weekends and Hollidays

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Really love this place. Very green, a lot variety of trees and birds. Lot of information of history, tree and other things.
All of the is friendly and helpful. Good place to bring kids.
Will return and spend more time for more detail exploration.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: The Singapore Botanic Gardens was successfully inscribed as Singapore's first UNESCO World Heritage Site on 4 July 2015. WOW! What a beautiful site. Luckily, my sister was my local guide and we managed to cover lots of ground in the couple of hours. It__ easily accessible by MRT. Do go there early or late in the afternoon to avoid the hot tropical sun. There are restaurants and cafes around too so you can relax after walking around. My favorites are the National Orchid Garden and the Swings Garden!!! The garden is huge and I__l definitely check it out for that places I missed next time round. ____

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Absolutely beautiful.

This massive (by Singapore_ standards) gardens is great for clocking steps while enjoying the varied flora and fauna.

Feast your eyes on the amazing variety of flowering and non-flowering plants, accompanied by squirrels, chickens and the occasional Komodo dragons.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: One of the best Botanic Gardens that I've ever seen! Saw some big lizards and an otter family there! Super clean and the directions through the gardens are very good. Lots of seating available too.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Very nice place to go for a walk or run. There are many activities on weekends , you can see more people bringing their dogs for a walk , Picnic near orchid garden , many restaurants to hang out there too. Enough parking for car and motorcycles . At the swan lake , you can find 2 white swans gliding gracefully around the pond . It__ really a beautiful park that I enjoyed very much in singapore .

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: The botanic gardens are really beautiful. So many different plants, flowers, shrubs and trees to see, with delightful water features and overhangs with different creepers growing off it. There are little lakes of water in different areas. Overall, the botanic gardens are very pretty and well maintained, and we even saw a resident rooster, his wife the hen, and their three little chicks. On the day we went, it rained lightly the whole time, but of course being Singapore, it was not cold at all, and in my case, I loved the rain. It was not a downpour, so was very pleasant to walk in. It deserves all the accolades and excellent reviews. We spent an hour wandering around the main garden before buying a ticket $15 for the orchid garden when it opened at 9am. Really superb displays of these fascinating flowers. We thoroughly enjoyed our visit and would highly recommended.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Absolutely stunning gardens, could spend two days there. The orchid garden is definitely worth it too! You'll spot fish, turtles, lizards, chickens, roosters, birds etc. Can have brunch/food within the gardens too

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: So happy we ended up going here! Really lovely gardens to stroll around - We went into the orchid garden which was around 15SGD which was well worth it! Honestly felt this was nicer than going to the Flower dome in gardens by the bay, a lot quieter and better value. Would come again!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: a beautiful park that can be found in the middle of the city. The best time to visit this location is in the afternoon, some people have picnics with their families, jogging or walking with their pets. No entry tickets.I like walking in this clean garden

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Amazing and peaceful place. Great place to calm your mind. Lots of plants and trees to observe. Can go on a long walk around the whole place. We also visited the place to see ' trees of the world ', but it wasn't worth it.   I personally did not like it.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Love these botanic gardens! So huge and such a variety of sub-gardens to explore! There are waterfalls and flowers and birds... could spend all day here! And don't miss the National Orchid Garden - stunning!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
It was really beautiful. The majority of areas are dog friendly, just a few that can't be accessed which are clearly marked.
We had a wonderful morning!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Serene, soothing, refreshing, informative, connecting with nature, amazing landscaping, detox, I can go on and on and on.

A must visit place when you want to disconnect and relax.

You would need minimum half a day to explore the entire place so plan accordingly

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Many areas to explore. Big and beautiful garden. There's pond, waterfall, gazebo, etc. So many breed of orchids and other perfume smelling flowers. There's herbs too. Many people there for sightseeing, walking and jogging. A lot of oxygen here to share. There's even shops and many cafes inside Botanic Gardens.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Excellent garden. Probably the best (free) public facility I__e been to in a very long time. Lots of walking, fantastic hours, not too many bugs, and beautiful landscaping.

Highly recommended!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Great park.
Highly recommend.
I entered via the learning entrance, hence passed through the Ginger Garden to National Orchid Garden. Took us 2 hours at the Orchid park as there are so many pretty orchids

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: It's a beautiful serene place with lots of greenery and flowers.. big green pastures... Perfect for a family picnic and also lot of restaurants to eat out! Definitely a Must Visit!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: So happy I visited this garden. I like looking at the huge trees & flowers while hiking. I can't wait to come back here again. Make sure to take a photo of the map at the entrance for the toilets directory.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Awesome place to jog, read a book, relax and take a stroll! Saw so much wildlife here! Even lots of great plants and places to take a picture! I could rest here all evening! So nice :)

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Great place to spend a quite morning. Even better when it is cloudy and right after the rain has stopped. The entire place feels fresh and the aroma of the wet earth is very uplifting to the senses. Lots of nice exhibits within the gardens are a good way to spend time. Nice location to picnic during non rainy days and well connected to public transport.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
My No.1 garden in Singapore.
Throughout the whole of singapore, there's nothing can compare with this national park "Botanic Garden", full of various types of plants, well-organized and great environments with not so crowded walking pathways.
Enjoy your visit, my friend. You will not regret visiting this heaven in Singapore!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Great for morning walks/ jogs with kids or pets. Some nice alfresco dining near Learning Forest. Also has an amazing collection of Orchids and rare tropical flora in the Singapore Orchid Gardens.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Superb garden to visit at any time.

After a long walk from the MRT exit, comes the Orchid Garden which is a must-visit place.

This place is a UNESCO heritage and that is another reason to visit.

Also, this place is quite vast, so you might have to visit multiple times to cover it all.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Even if you're not really into gardening, this is a must-visit.   The variety of orchids is astounding.  It's super relaxing to simply walk around - it's like a walk through a rainforest.  Plan for at least 3 hours.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
A great green space to walk around and sit and people watch on the weekend.
Easily accessible by public transport and free entry, excluding Orchid Garden which was free for locals but SG$15 for tourists
We spent a few hours walking around and didn't get bored or see the same thing twice.
Great place for young and old

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Beautiful and peaceful.
Great place to have a walk, have a run, rest.
The entrance is free just for the Orchidee garden you have to pay.
Lots of beautiful plants, birds and ponds.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A place that keeps it promise to visitors on what to expect within the gardens. Caters to all walk of life. The_Singapore Botanic Gardens_is a_163-year-old tropical garden and is one of three gardens and the only tropical garden to be honored as a UNESCO_World Heritage Site.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A very peaceful place to hike among one of the many trails and paths inside the park. You can also purchase tickets to enter the Orchid Garden. An overall free attraction with beautiful scenery best suited to early morning walks. It get's pretty hot in the mid day.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Visited today and found the grounds breathtakingly lush and manicured. The Orchid Garden is a must...although blooms at their best March to May.
However, the pick up taxi service needs to be addressed. The designated taxi stand is ineffective.
The taxi CALL  button doesn't work. The taxi phone contact at the stand is invalid. The txt number is invalid. You could wait  definitely and not get a ride.
There were others waiting and after 45 minutes we asked for help at the Visitor Service.  Success.
Our taxi driver Informed us that the Taxi Stand is not for pickups. Management could address the misinformation in support of their visitors.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Very fun experience!

There was quite a lot of wildlife when I went there. I spotted otters napping and playing near a pond, and monitor lizards in the water (in another pond, don't worry). There were also chickens running around! While I was walking along a path, I noticed that there was a big bird perched on a branch and was grooming its feathers. I'm thankful that I managed to see all of this close up!

It was extremely humid, but I would recommend wearing long pants because of the mosquitoes. Bring an umbrella along as well - not just to help protect yourself against the rain, but to protect yourself from the sweltering heat of the sun too.

I went to the orchid garden and it was beautiful. Do expect to walk quite a bit before getting there (est. 10mins). You can see a variety of orchids, and there's also an indoor exhibition (with air con! very important point) with many big orchids too.

Nearest MRT: Botanic Gardens

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Such a nice place! We were not sure if we should visit it as the nice lady at the tourist center in Singapore told us the kids would be bored. But we really enjoyed it, the plants and even animals as we got to see lots of lizards and squirrels. I loved the orchid garden, it was amazing. We walked a lot and spent the entire day here.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: What a treasure the Botanic Gardens are! The price is right if you just want to walk around. It's FREE! There is a fee to go through the orchid garden, but it is well worth it. The entire park is a great way to spend the afternoon. Stay as long as you like. It is kid friendly.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Had a great time there with my friends. Good place to hang out with families and go out to have a walk or picnic. Highly recommend the orchid garden. The entrance fee was pretty cheap and we spent around 1 hour + there.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful gardens, and quite extensive too. There are some cafs and an orchid garden as well. I got married here, so obviously the Botanic Gardens gets 5 stars from me!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: I had a wonderful time at the Singapore Botanic Gardens! This expansive green space offers a peaceful retreat from the hustle and bustle of the city, with lush gardens and impressive tree canopies that provide plenty of shade. I particularly enjoyed the National Orchid Garden, which is home to an incredible variety of orchids, and the Jacob Ballas Children's Garden, which is perfect for families. The staff were friendly and helpful, and the facilities were clean and well-maintained. Overall, a must-visit destination in Singapore for nature lovers and anyone looking for a relaxing outdoor experience.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Even getting caught in the rain showers didn__ dampen my visit here.   I only hit the Orchid Garden, but that was enough for me.  Beautiful varieties on display!

Plenty more to visit on my next trip there!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
I love this botanic garden. It became my regular places to walk around since pandemic. The design of the gardens I would say really at the top in my opinion. It is one of three  gardens and the only tropical garden to be honored as a UNESCO World Heritage Site.

Here introduce some of the areas you should not miss: Swan Lake >> Heritage Garden (Sundial Garden) >> Bandstand >>Ginger Garden >> Palm Valley >> Symphony Lake >> red brick path >>eco-lake >> ethnobotany garden >> end point is visitor center & NPark headquarters. If you walk in this route, should be within one& half hours.

There are 2 -3 swan in the Swan lake & 2-3 black swan at Eco-lake. Lately I only saw 2 swan in the center island of the swan lake and no black swan in the eco-lake.

If you walk pass by the red bricks path, you can smell very nice pandan leave fragrance & jasmine flower fragrance, and other herbs that I can't name them.

The garden also has eco rubbish bins, auto grass cut machines.

Not to mention the rain forest walk is funny and bring you different experience, butt it only open from 7am to 7pm.

The garden in most of the areas are free. If you are interested to visit the orchid garden, there is a entry fee you need to pay. Enjoy!

Some of the pics I shared here was a event during 2022 Singapore national day. Enjoyed the garden competition display!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Nice place to take picture, walk and do some light jog. But some areas like the small ponds starting to get dirty. Hopefully they could maintain the cleanliness of the park to remain its beauty

Ps. The mask only taken off during photoshoot!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Wonderful place to visit when you plan to have long layover in Singapore. We took private car but there is a possibility of train too. It's free for all except the Orchid garden has a token entry fee.  Have a look at the map and go systematically. You could enjoy the pristine (man made ) but amazingly natural landscaped and well maintained garden.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Big, very well organised and clean. Impressive variety of plants and I really like that they have multiple education centres. Lots of clean toilets and conveniently-placed restaurants. Can get quite confusing but fortunately lots of signboards and map spots around to help with wayfinding. Food prices are fairly expensive. Good range of gifts in the gift shop.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Must visit place if you__e in Singapore. Entry to the Botanic Gardens is free except the Orchid Garden. But it__ worth the visit. Beautiful and you will be spending a lot of time taking photos too.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Singapore Botanic Garden is a serene place where you can seek refuge from the urban populated areas of central Singapore. The gardens themselves are easy accessible by MRT, and they are vast so you can easily use many hours in here. My wife and I enjoyed walking around experiencing the different gardens and forests, but we feel that, apart from the crown jewel of the gardens which is The Orchid Garden, it seemed like any other botanic garden the world over. So if you're not ready to spend 15$ each on the Orchid Garden, and you're not a botanic enthusiasts, then it's not a must on your touristic visit to Singapore.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Really big park that i wish i have it in my country. You can jog for 10 km++ circle around the park.
Mostly free except the orchid garden.
There is theatre in the middle of park for show or conser.
Sometimes you can see animals like squirrels, turtles, chicken wandering around.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Singapore Botanical Gardens is an absolute must visit.  A huge beautiful area full of as much flora & fauna as you can imagine.

There are huge green grassy areas perfect to play sports or have family time or even a picnic.  Tons of trees of all species, many different kinds of flowers and there is also a large body of water which usually has ducks and other wildlife.  I even saw a huge monitor lizard.

The national orchid garden is also inside as well as a Raffles Building, a food court, sports facilities and more.

Free entry. Has MRT near.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: These gardens are spectacular. The Orchid garden is a must see. Also unexpected animals such as otters monkeys and monitor lizards are ever present. Allow at least 3 hours...

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Incredible place to wander: for free!!! Really enjoyed my visit here. Sadly didn__ see any wild monkeys. Lots of shade around too for the punishing sun. Incredibly well-maintained.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Every third Saturday is an opportunity for a guided tour. We lucked into a tour and it was wonderful, adding great value to our experience. Don__ miss the magnificent __ool building_, recently refurbished to the tune of $35,000,000

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Amazing for naturists, bird watchers, animal lovers. Come here dor a great exercise but be surrounded by beautiful nature. Been here twice and both experiences were amazing!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A wonderful park to take a stroll whether your day is sunny or with a bit of Asian rain. If you are attracted to plants, trees or flowers, the park is your treasure. Located not very far from the downtown area, take a taxi or MRT and you will be there shortly.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: The Singapore Botanic Gardens are a wonderful location to take a stroll, relax, and behold the beautifully kept landscape with its flowers, ponds, and animals. Large parts of the garden are free of charge to enter. There are some exhibitions, like the Orchid garden, for which you need to buy a ticket. There are many discounts for locals, senior citizens, as well as students.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: The Singapore Botanic Gardens have something for everyone. Great variety of native flora with helpful and informative placards providing historical context and background on the species, etc. I especially appreciate the focus on conservation and climate response throughout the gardens. Be sure to check out the Curtain of Roots and Rainforest walk. A treasure in the midst of the big city.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: The Gardens are spectacular. I expected to enjoy them but I didn't expect to love them! Huge trees, delicate orchids, exotic climates- it had it all. I highly recommend it! While the overall Gardens are free, there is a fee for the Orchid Gardens. Totally worth it. If you're hungry, check out Priv! The cafe is at the entrance to the Gardens. The food was fresh, delicious and plentiful!____

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Great relaxing space with immaculate gardens. Plenty of wildlife to spot & another worthwhile visit, to escape the hubbub of the city.  Orchid Garden is worth the charge, considering the gardens as a whole are free admission.
Highly recommended.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Absolutely beautiful experience. There are roosters running around and the trails are easy and accessible. I highly recommend for anyone visiting Singapore.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Visited on 1-Jan-22.  A nice cool day (raining last night) for taking a walk. Like many people, I went to SBG. For this visit, I wanted to check out the National Orchids Garden (entry charge applies) where the VIP orchids are kept. Note: mosquitoes in this area.

There are many other orchids in the Sembcorp cool house.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: As far as botanical gardens go around the world and we've been to many, this one was a little underwhelming. We had 2 kids 5 and under, they had a play on a couple of small play equipment set ups inclusive of a Flying fox, treehouse and very small in ground trampoline. The water feature is nice. Would spend an hour max here. The staff were delightful and very helpful.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Nice lush garden with lots of different plants. National Orchid Garden is also quite nice, especially the cool house is perfect for a short relaxation from the hot outside temperatures

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A truly stunning place to find in such a bustling modern city! A vast and peaceful gardens with a variety of areas to explore and relax in. The gardens are also well served with a good selection of places to eat and refresh yourself with a cooling drink. Two tips, take plenty to drink and make sure you have a camera or a phone with a camera built in it as you'll want to take plenty of beautiful pictures.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Well maintained, well planned and properly cared botanic garden.
Visited here few times while living in SG. One of my favorite places to take scroll while enjoying smells of trees, plants and flowers.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
We didn't manage to cover the entire gardens as they are huge, but from the small part we've been to we saw magical flowers and amazing nature and greenery!
Very clean and beautiful park.
Take in consideration that you're going to walk a lot.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: I woukd recommend this to anyone with an interest in gardens or would just like a stroll. Very well kept and many different aspects to it. Biggest bonus, it's free to enter. A highly recommended trip.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Still the best park in Singapore. Smack right beside Orchard Rd, it's really a convenient place to go pinicking, running, walk, and maybe just chill.

Although I feel its best to never go on a Sunday.  It's over crowded....

Best part, it's free of charge.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Large garden, well maintained, and has huge variety of plants in different settings.  Special orchid section (National Orchid Gallery) is worth visiting even though it has an entrance fee while the Botanic Garden itself is free admission.

Lots of grassy areas for family picnic, several km worth of walkways (some shady), a couple of restaurants to grab food and drinks.

Easily accessible by car (several car parks), busses, and MRT (Botanic Garden - Downtown/Circle Lines).  Park entrance is just steps outside the MRT exit.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
The most stunning botanic gardens I have ever seen. You could easily spend the whole day (or even more time!) to discover each corner of this huge garden.

There is also the "National Orchid Garden", which costs around S$ 15 for foreign visitors (I visited it in the past, and it is rather expensive for what it is, so I would recommend to only visit the free areas of the botanic garden)

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Visited Singapore botanic gardens after ages. Lovely to watch an Abba concert performed by the Music and Dance company. The kids had a welcome relaxing break from studying for their exams.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Gorgeous gardens, beautifully kept and maintained. Plenty of path ways throughout. Gardens have many different spaces with a wide variety of plant and tree types, a lot of wildlife scattered around too. Just a shame we couldn't spend longer there. Loved the orchid gardens the most, absolutely massive variety in orchids

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Recommend to go on weekday, weekend quite a lot of people.
Spend your time there enjoy the scenery and if lucky you can spot some wildlife.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Place have many interesting features, flowers, Lake n lots of resting place with benches.  Can also see big chameleon taking short cut by crossing over on the footpath

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Probably the largest Botanical Gardens I__e seen.
I am rating 4 stars because upon entering there are really no directions or guidance on where to go or what attractions/gardens are to see. We kept walking thinking we would see a help desk but it__ not till further in that you will see signs pointing to __isitors desk_.
You can choose to walk any route you wish.
Very picturesque.
Take water! It__ very hot in there and we did not see many water stations or shops.
It__ free in cost unless you want to visit the orchard garden.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Botanic gardens that is quite large and they are various garden in it, more interesting is the orchid garden the flowers all fresh and the colors are very beautiful that I have never seen, this place is suitable for exercise, jogging, brisk walk relaxing or picnic.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: This park opens 24hrs and there are many securities camera too. Clean toilets and shops for water and drinks, restaurants. Absolutely beautiful park! A sports drink was $3.5.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: First I'd like to say that I was surprised that there was no admission fee to get in. That being said there is an admission fee for special exhibits, like the rare orchid exhibit. The garden is beautiful, relaxing and emaculate. I could have spent all day there.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Loved the gardens. Wonderfully kept and some fantastic views. Wish we had more time to see everything. I guess the trade-off is that grounds keepers were everywhere.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful botanic garden. If you want you can spend the whole day here. The rainforest walk is beautiful and the national orchid garden is great. Really recommend

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Must visit when in Singapore. A great place to exercise, socialize, play, learn, relax. I liked most the Evolution Garden. You can easily spend the whole day here, or just few hours if you prefer. There are shops and restaurants inside the Gardens.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: This is a nice place to enjoy the nature particularly trees and plants. There is no entrance fee. The visitors are free to explore the garden but only by foot. I think it needs more than one day to completely explore the garden. You can reach the garden easily using MRT since there is a station next to it. For you who love nature and physical activity especially walking or running, this place is a must visit.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: I__ truly at a loss for words for this place but I__l try my best. This garden is absolutely spectacular from the lakeside trails to the breathtaking orchid gardens. I love going to botanic gardens and make it a point to visit one in every place I travel to, and this one is inarguably the best one yet. If you__e on vacation in Singapore please visit the Singapore Botanic Gardens.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Amazing gardens __
There is so much to see in the wonderful Botanic Gardens.The gardens are huge. The garden is free everyday. Reaching the Gardens is easy, by train or bus.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Such an amazing place to go for a relaxing stroll with my family.  Lots of greeneries & beautiful flowers to admire.  Feeling so rejuvenated & will definitely make it a monthly affair to return again and again _

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Beautiful and serene. Must visit.
Do plan and spend enough time since there are multiple places to visit and garden is huge. Would recommend buying the tickets to orchid garden

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: I loved it. Full of flora and interesting descriptions, especially the ones about the medicinal plants. It also features a lot of fauna and I got the chance to see a very cute family of otters playing in the pond!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Great place, Beautiful landscape flowers. A nice picnic place for family or friends get together. The Orchid gardens was splendid.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
The national orchid garden is having free admission for Singapore residents during the June school holidays (should be 26 June). Lovely place. The sembcorp cool house is a mini version of the rainforest dome of the gardens by the bay.
Other areas of the botanic gardens are also fun to explore, even for parents with younger children in prams, although the weather could be uncomfortably warm n humid...

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
The botanical gardens in Singapore are beautiful and expansive, with a huge variety of different natural niches. They are also home to many kinds of animals that just roam around the area, from lizards to monkeys.
Areas for children are also available, like the amazing Jacob Ballas garden, and sometimes you can catch a concert at thr symphony lake. Absolutely gorgeous.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Must visit place in Singapore. You can get lots public transport to the Botanic Gardens and then the long walk starts. So much trees and plants are planted and preserved in the heart of this little city state. There's little plaques giving us all sorts of information about the plants. There's plenty of seats for visitors who are taking a long walk or you can sit by the little water pond. Must visit if you are in Singapore.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Great garden with large collection of flowers, trees etc and lovely walks around the lakes. Good cafes also around the grounds. Easily reached by the MTR.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Botanical gardens is just lovely and so serene to walk or exercise. Great place to capture shots of flora & fauna or even the monitor lizards!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A wonderful place that makes you forget you are in a giant city. There are many paths you can take. You can easily spent half a day here walking trough nature. I would really recommend to walk the Rainforest trail. You find many small animals here

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
I absolutely loved this place. We took the MRT from the city and got a taxi back as it is quite far from Marina Bay etc. As a result it is much more peaceful and there  are far fewer tourists here. Especially when compared to other similar attractions like Gardens by the Bay.

The Botanic gardens are scenic, well maintained and home to a number of individual smaller gardens, facilities and restaurants. We had a disappointing experience at Bee__ Knees so I wouldn__ recommend eating there.

There is a lot to do and see but I would head to the Orchid Garden (paid entry) where we spend almost 2 hours. The place is relatively big and we were tired after walking around at midday. There are so many beautiful and unique orchids. I thoroughly recommend for plant lovers and anyone looking for a beautiful and peaceful escape from the city.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Over 1000 species of orchids here and they are gorgeously displayed. Spent a couple hours and enjoyed every moment.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Gorgeous gardens! The orchid garden is so worth it. Not only is it beautiful, but it is an excellent reprieve from the heat! There is also a well appointed gift shop.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful, lush green and extremely well maintained garden. Love going here for picnics with family and friends. Restaurant inside also good.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Good but the lake is less maintained.
I walked from end to end so tiring.
My leg mau patah lah. It's huge park and the path is circular not a straight line _
But no worries they have refreshments and resto inside.
Nice experience after all. Just wish the weather could be cooler would be perfect.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Utterly amazing that you can have such a big, beautiful open green space so close to such a high end city but then again this is Singapore that we're talking about and if anyone knows how to do beautiful green spaces, it's Singapore.  A simply breath taking garden on an immense scale, possibly the finest garden that we have been to.  It is absolutely stunning.  It is really easy to get to on the metro.  There are water fountains and toilets and beautiful air conditioned shops (to escape the heat) and a MacDonalds - we had a macflurry for a treat and it was delicious.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Gardens aren't my thing. But you don't say 'no' when you're visiting a city that you don't live in. Especially when it's a UNESCO World Heritage site. Period.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
It is a must to visit these garden. Cool beautiful and full of history and wildlife.
See how many monitor lizards you can spot up in the trees sunbathing and the otters too

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: An oasis in the middle of the vivid city. The gardeners are very kind and helpful with interesting information about the plants. The entry fee for the orchid garden is worth being paid!! Such an amazing place!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: I last visited this place more than 10 years ago. Decided to start off early but if you are using CTE make sure it is past 9.30am. Beware of ERP charges. Fortunately found a signage 'CLUNY Food Court'. We were there about 10.30am. Good for breakfast but it has to be after 1130 for lunch when more stalls are opened. Carpark is in front of Food Court. Must try the Groupa Fish porridge ($11.50 per bowl and good for 1 pax), Laksa and Ayam/Ikan Penyet. Pricing on the high side but food is really nice. Come on good food must pay lah. Of course there will be drinks stall to fill your crave for coffeeshop coffee. After bf/lunch, take a short walk to the 'Healing Garden'. After all the holes in your pockets, you really need healing. It is a wonderful place to be at peace after bf/lunch make you so much poorer. Ha ha ha. There is a saying. "A picture speaks a thousand words", so I am going to post pictures instead of writing.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Very large and beautiful garden. It's open to the public so no fees or anything. There's a seed bank building that's worth checking out, as well as the durian exhibit at the time.

There's lizards and different species of birds living in the garden itself.
It's very well maintaineda and clean.

Best to do the garden not during midday since it's completely outdoors.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Love our very own Botanical Gardens. Many different species of trees to be observed. Nice to learn something new from there every time I go

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Ensure you bring children to the Jacob Ballas Gardens as adults are denied entry if no children accompany them. Good safety measure for protecting children. There are some play spots for younger kids, but maximum age allowed is 14 years old. Parents could use these gardens to enable their kids to see more plants, especially those which are important for consumption/environment protection or identifying those which are poisonous. There are also education programmes for large group activities, which require earlier bookings.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Lovely and huge! A great place for a nice long walk. The orchid garden is also very nice. There is a nice gift shop as well. Really enjoyed walking around, even though it was raining.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Nice experience. Though the walk is  more. I suggest go in a good weather. Must visit is orchid garden. Some pics from orchid garden are attached.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful natural gardens not far from marina bay by metro. Free entry and a beautiful walk in nature. Highly recomment and inside is the orchid garden

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
A super nice place to spend an afternoon with friends and family. The orchids are lovely. The design of the Orchid garden is good in a sense that we did not need to walk the same path again, and could go all the way down and saw almost everything.
We had a great time there. Highly recommend.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Such a well-maintained garden with various species of beautiful flowers and plants. There are many pathways to explore it well and huts to take short rest.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Truly enjoyed our visit to Singapore Botanic Gardens after 26 years of being away. It is amazing the these gardens continue to offer such a wide variety of plants and flowers in such a large and well-maintained area. Our focus was Natuonal Orchid Gardens and we truly enjoyed special exhibits such as Burkhill Hall, Sembcorp Cool House, and Tan Hoon Siang Mist House even though I posted pictures of these exhibits in separate reviews. Will definetely be coming to back to see everything. It's hard to see it all in one day.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Although not that big for a botanical garden they are certainly beautiful. These gardens are a beautiful nature escape from the city. We also spotted squirrels, a giant water monitor, and lots of birds. Unfortunately our trip was kind of spoiled though because it rained heavily and they closed off most of the tracks even after the rain stopped.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A really enjoyable walk in Singapore. The garden has many things to offer, lots to see, lots of rest areas. Great for families

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
A great place to spend a few hours away from the hustle and bustle of the city. We were there about three hours and didn't get round more than half.

We spent over an hour at the children's garden, which was very varied and entertaining. There was a play area, a waterfall, a skywalk, a little maze, plus a little brook, and a slightly pricey caf just at the entrance. (Price of entry? "Just a high five," said the kind lady at the entrance __)

Maybe it's because we'd just come from Borneo, but I was kind of surprised by the gardens' UNESCO status. They're good ... but not THAT good. Still a very pleasant way to while away an afternoon though.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A beautiful garden, which have developed a lot since my childhood days. An ideal place to spend a Sunday morning with friends & family.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Second time of visiting, beautiful, stunning, amazing just a few words to describe it, my favourite place is the Orchid Garden a small entry charges but worth every $, it's alway's worth going I've never been disappointed!!!!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
I just had to share lovely pics and videos of the Zouk otter family in Singapore Botanic Gardens. They are really a celebrity family with bodyguards, paparazzi and fans following them everywhere they go!

We have heard stories of how people have come too close to the otters and how people have been bitten. Otters are wild animals after all and we have to give them a wide berth and learn to live in harmony with them. Like it or not, they are here to stay.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Visited on 31/07/2022,is a sunny__ day. And it happened that the Singapore Garden Festival is having the festival here. All the winning Orchids are displaying in the National Orchid Garden so is free admission starting from 30/07-09/08/2022 for local residents including Work Permit Holders. From Botanic Garden MRT station Exit A will be Bukit Timah Gate and a Visitor Service counter,there's a Water dispenser and Drinks vending machine. From there turn left walked up will be Eco Lake and so lucky to see a Black Swan. From Eco Lake continued walking will reached Jacob Ballas Children's Garden. I have my brunch at Little Spot Cafe, is just 1minute walked to Jacob Ballas Children's Garden and Visitor center.

After brunch walked out will be Eco Lake turn left will be Ethnobotany Garden. Where's the Stone Murals are located and Ethnobotany Centre too. Am really enjoying 'admiring' the stone murals and thumbs up for the craftsmen for the hard work. Ethnobotany Centre, explores Plants that how South East Asia's people used for living. Is 2-storey air-condition centre. So a must visit for gaining our knowledge of how people make use of the plants for living and at the same time cool our body from the __.

Walked quite far reached Fragrant Garden, never smell any fragrant at all but according to Google search at night time then can smell the nice fragrant.

Next to Fragrant Garden is Healing Garden. It huge as have different zone herbs and spice for different body parts,I just explored half of it only as wanted to go National Orchid Garden.

After Nassim Gate Visitor Centre walked further down is National Orchid Garden and surrounding it is Symphony Lake and Ginger Garden. Further down will be Gallop Extension. National Orchid Garden, is a must to visit of viewing different types of Orchids. Spend 2-3hrs there but I missed out Sembcorp Cool House as is the other side but I lost my way.

After National Orchid Garden,next to it is Ginger Garden where the little 'Cave waterfall' is located.

Then further up is saw the small bonsai garden, small Cactus garden. Then saw the Bandstand, Lawn E. The Tembusan Heritage Tree where our $5 notes' tree. Have took a photo of it with the $5 note. Swan Lake under the lake there are 'water grasslands' so beautiful. Then walked to Tanglin Gate to take free shuttle bus(specially for Singapore Garden Festival) to Botanic Garden MRT station.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A national park. Rather rigid garden. Strictly no playing of sport game, frisbee, drone, kite flying etc... Any event must be due to prior approval from the npark. Do not occupy the whole gazebo for your own. Picnic allowed.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: This is definitely __  must visit if you are in Singapore. We enjoyed the walk in the park and it is really chill. The park Is pet friendly as  well.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Fantastic landscape. I had a cup of capuchino in a beautiful coffee shop. Chill Music, fresh atmosphere, good coffee, and a small rain, perfect morning.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A very huge garden! It is a UNESCO world heritage site and one of the best botanical gardens I ever visited. It's free and you can spend the whole day if you want to explore it throughly!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A lovely place to visit, for jogging, tracking, picnic or just want to conect with the nature. Best time to visit is in the morning, the sun shine is warm the air is fresh. This is a free place to visit, a tourist can try to visit this place to see the animals like swan, birds, turtles, squirels, and pretty buterfly. I visit this place on december unfortunetly it was rain so better next time check the wheater prediction to make sure the right time to visit this place

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Just beautiful!
Take a break from eating and the heat and visit paradise!
Singapore is the best city where urban meets gardens!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Very nice and well maintained garden. I spent there more than 4 hours slow walking. A lot of paths some time like a maze.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
The Singapore Botanic Gardens is a long-time favorite for a lot of runners. It__ built to be consistent for runners doing varied distance runs across a variety of runs over varied terrain.

There have been a few updates to the Gardens, but the major change from previous models is the Gallop Extension. The Singapore Botanic Gardens is 100% UNESCO World Heritage Site which is more supported than past generations of this botanical garden.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
One of the large parks located near the city center and easily accessible by public transport. The park is very well maintained with many open spaces and greenery attractions such as swan lake, eco lake, symphony lake, and ginger garden. The National Orchid Garden is one of the highlights of the garden. The entrance fee to the botanic garden is free but you need to pay S$5 (local) or S$15 (standard/non-local) if you also want to visit orchid garden. Rainforest trail is a short trail but quite serene to stroll along. Bandstand is another highlight of the botanic garden where proposals or pre-wedding photoshoots were taken lol.

Due to its open space, it's best to visit either in the early morning or late evening. If you prefer to go in the afternoon, perhaps choose the cloudy days as it could be quite hot.

It's one of my favorites parks in Singapore which is beautiful, serene, well-maintained, easily accessible, and most of the time, it's >95% safe for female solo explorer/walker/hiker

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: My favorite place ever. Such a comfortable place to walk around, have a picnic and good talk with your love ones.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Wonderful, spectacular botanic gardens. Beautifully maintained and manicured. Amazing selection of exotic plants from around the world.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: This Garden is curated especially for all flora lovers and plants lovers. I highly recommend National Orchid Garden. Very beautiful orchids are there and highly informative.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful place with Huge garden, please bring food items incase if you plan for day outing. Orchard gardens has ticket counter we need tickets to enter.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
One of the best botanical gardens I've been to!
Truly worth of a day visit.
Do not miss the Orchid Gardens!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Singapore Botanic Gardens (SBG) is beautiful all year round, free for all to enjoy!  In Dec, there is the __rees of the World_ Christmas light up.  As Singapore is very safe, the gardens is lovely to visit at night especially during the Dec Christmas light up.  The decorations are beautiful and the weather is cooler too.

In the day, there are many people doing exercises and walks in the park.  There are several regular exercise groups too.  Many also bring their dogs for walks and play.  On some weekends, there are concerts held at the Symphony Stage, where families gather for picnics while enjoying the performances.  The Orchid Garden within the SBG houses many beautiful orchids.

SBG is big and there is much to explore and learn.  There is the Learning Forest, and the new Gallop Extension.  There are souvenir shops where we can pick up nice gifts to bring home.  There are a few lovely restaurants within SBG, from casual to fine dining.  SBG truly deserves its name as a UNESCO heritage site.

SBG is easily accessible via public transport.  One of the main gate (Bukit Timah Gate) is at the entrance of Botanic Gardens MRT station via Exit A.  Tanglin Gate is also walking distance from the new Napier MRT station. There are also many parking spots for those who prefer to drive.  Always dress cool and comfortable when visiting SBG in the day.  I will never get tired of visiting SBG. __

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful gardens and free. Can easily spend a day there. The National Orchid Garden is payable but well worth a visit.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Well havent seen much but i do know this place has alot of resting areas and quite beauriful tbh.Does have a pond then there would be a resting area which is huge.Not much photos i have unfortunately but maybe someday ill bring in more.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Green and serene. Singapore really take a good care of their gardens, including this old botanical garden. Very well preserved with plenty zones to be explore.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful UNESCO garden with many different species of plants and flora with many different birds nesting. Can be crowded during weekends. Family friendly.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A relaxing place to visit that offers a change in pace. We only had 3 hours so we walked thru the "forest walk" which is a board walk kind of activity. Really nice and only took about 20 to 30 minutes. Then we explored the orchid garden (small extra fee) which was amazing. Next we wondered thru the gift shop before having a light lunch at Halia (we had made a booking which was wise). A fantastic morning in Singapore.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Botanic garden Singapore, world heritage UNESCO. Beautiful garden, large trees, very special orchid park and a lot of different animals. Great half-day trip.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful botanical gardens that are on the UNESCO heritage list for a reason. Quite a lot of wildlife from lizards to turtles and also monkeys and otters. The different biomes are great, like the swamp area and the rainforest.  The one place I can highly recommend is the orchid garden, although you need to pay its amazing (see my account for the review for more details).

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: So many plants and good place for exercise, especially in morning and afternoon. Its a good spot for taking photo too. You can find some animals around the park as well.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Find your zen: It's a good place to visit on weekday mornings. Keep your eyes peeled for squirrels! I spotted 3 of them but am not always fast enough to take a photo. Bring sunblock and water.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: What a vast land area! Loved it here. The plant parent in me couldn't get over how nice it was to be so close ro nature. I liked that there was an area for prayer plants and calatheas. I was super amazed at so many plants and trees. The Orchid place was lovely.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
The Singapore Botanic Gardens is a 163-year-old tropical garden located at the fringe of the Orchard Road shopping district in Singapore. It is one of three gardens, and the only tropical garden, to be honoured as a UNESCO World Heritage Site. The Botanic Gardens has been ranked Asia's top park attraction since 2013, by TripAdvisor Travellers' Choice Awards. It was declared the inaugural Garden of the Year, International Garden Tourism Awards in 2012.

The Botanic Gardens was founded at its present site in 1859 by the Agri-horticultural Society. It played a pivotal role in the region's rubber trade boom in the early twentieth century when its first scientific director, Henry Nicholas Ridley, headed research into the plant's cultivation. By perfecting the technique of rubber extraction, which is still in use today, and promoting its economic value to planters in the region, rubber output expanded rapidly. At its height in the 1920s, the Malayan peninsula cornered half of the global latex production.

The National Orchid Garden, which is located within the main gardens, is at the forefront of orchid studies and a pioneer in the cultivation of hybrids, complementing the nation's status as a major exporter of cut orchids. Aided by the equatorial climate, it houses the largest orchid collection of 1,200 species and 2,000 hybrids.

Early in the nation's independence, Singapore Botanic Gardens' expertise helped to transform the island into a tropical Garden City, an image and moniker for which the nation is widely known. In 1981, the hybrid climbing orchid, Vanda Miss Joaquim, was chosen as the country's national flower. Singapore's "orchid diplomacy" honours visiting head of states, dignitaries, and celebrities by naming its finest hybrids after them; these are displayed at its popular VIP Orchid Gardens.

The Gardens is opened from 5 a.m. to 12 midnight daily and is free to enter, except for the National Orchid Garden.[6] More than 10,000 species of flora are spread over its 82 hectares (200 acres) area, which is stretched vertically; the longest distance between the northern and southern ends is 2.5 km (1.6 mi). The Botanic Gardens receives about 4.5 million visitors annually.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Great exposure to the nature. The trail is shady. Beautiful mini waterfall for the kids. And lots and lots of stuff inside.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Amazing gardens showing off some beautiful flowers and the plants. Very educational and a nice place to unwind.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Delightful to walk through the park, clean and peaceful. Some wildlife on the way to the Orchid Gardens which for me was one highlight of the trip

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful garden with an amazing collection. Must visit when you are in Singapore. Time needed: At least 4-5hrs including the orchid garden.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A well maintained place to walk around if you can handle the heat. You may encounter otters and lizards hunting fishes. Quite a big place to explore. The Orchid Garden is not free to enter.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Very nice park  for walking around. Lots of trees and breathtaking view inside of park. It's most beautiful park in Singapore.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Nice place to enjoy nature and relax. Lots of nice plants and trees. You may jog and picnic here as long as you keep the environment clean. Not forgetting the air is so fresh. There are cafes too. Beautiful place. MRT - Botanic Garden.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: First of all, this wonderful place is free to visit. Then you go in and see a beautiful displ6of trees a d plants. Nice area for kids and cafe/ restaurant is well placed. A great place to visit.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Singapore must-do!! Beautifully landscaped and manicured gardens and most of the gardens there is no fee. The Orchid Garden we did $15 each to go see and it was more than worth the fee.  Likely the most established and well-kept orchid garden in the world!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Revisited this place since Covid19. Still a lovely place to meet friends and walk. A wide range of plants and trees in the entire parks for u to spend the whole morning and afternoon. Park worth visit again and again.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Safra members gets free access to orchid garden this season.
Cool house is great. Love all the micro orchids!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: This surprisingly sizeable scenic park is a must-visit for biophilics. This UNESCO world heritage site is located just five minutes away from the bustling Orchards road in the city's heart and within a few steps off the Botanic Gardens MRT. Some of the featured attractions in this botanical institute include the Ethnobotany Garden, the National orchid garden, and Jacob Balla's children's garden. There is a Ginger garden showcasing hundreds of species of gingers and related plants. Many trees growing here have 'name plates' describing their origin and botanical details. The sight of exotic plants like Tongkat Ali, Cocao, and Ackee always fills my heart with joy.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
The Botanic Gardens definitely has a special place in every true Singaporean as well as its historical place in the World.

Unlike the Gardens by the Bay, a modernistic attempt, Botanic Gardens is a repository of our nation's journey and milestones as a Garden City. This is where the first rubber trees and award winning orchids thrived.

For everyday Singaporeans, it is a place etched into our childhood, adult and senior years. Nostalgia is one motivation. Free entry a factor too. But the all-natural flora and fauna (yes there are) is a balm for visitors.

Best time to visit is early mornings or late evenings. Try to visit the library too.

And yes, either eat before visiting or BYO snacks. Insect repellant is advised.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Botanic Gardens is one of the best gardens in Singapore! It's a wonderful place to be in nature and to explore and understand the world of plants. Botanic Gardens have many different gardens along the routes such as the Evolution Garden, Healing Garden, Fragrant Garden and more! Each garden showcase a different set of plants catered specifically to the theme. You will not only gain a better understanding about the plants in each garden but also enjoy the sights and smells of each one. Do remember to bring along your insect repellent and a water bottle.

Recommended to visit at least twice because this is a huge place. Overall a very relaxing place to take a walk and be with nature!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: I love the botanic gardens in Singapore! It__ one of our favorite places to visit and we go there quite frequently. It__ a reasonably large park with a lot to see over a range of different landscapes and themes. You can go there again and again and keep finding something new and engaging. It__ also a great place for a leisurely walk or a challenging run, as it__ fairly hilly. It__ only around 4km in circumference but if you learn the paths through the park itself (the signs can be confusing since the paths tend to twist and turn a lot), you can get in even 15 or 20km with little repetition. In addition to the plants and flowers, there is also a wide variety of wildlife: birds, insects, reptiles, and even otters and monkeys. There are also places to eat, drink, and just take a rest. There is also the National Orchid Garden inside, as well as a variety of museums.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Hands down one of the most beautiful parks in Singapore, after Jurong Lake Gardens (hehe). It is the first UNESCO Heritage Site in Singapore, and is one of those parks where I grew up visiting. So many species of trees, flowers, and plants to see, as well as swans, monitor lizards, terrapins chickens and quails, not to mention spectacular water views and open grass areas for yoga or picnics. Did you know that within the National Orchid Garden there are over 1000 species and 2000 hybrids on display? Simply amazing.

If you have some spare time, walk around the garden and relax along the lake and watch children playing and running non stop.
Several gates, arches, artificial ponds and waterfall etc. We saw a huge monitor lizard crossing the way in a jiffy.
