Here, you can interact with animals, breath in fresh air (abit difficult with masks on now..) or even just look up at the beautiful sky!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: this place was really awesome!! Huge, clean, and beautiful __ we can find various kinds of trees here, I think they also have wild chicken?! Nearby the entrance of Botanic garden also have many restaurants and cafes. Recommendations for everyone is the simply bread in the cluny court.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Amazing. Highly recommended for visiting.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Best botanic garden I've ever seen.
You need at least half a day to see everything. The orchids garden is the best in the world

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Do visit the orchard garden, there is a newly furnished section. The whole area is practically filled with beautiful orchid flowers.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: An UNESCO heritage site.  Very beautiful garden.  Extensive orchid collection in its natural setting.  The place is well kept, neat as a pin.  Nice gift shop, nice restaurant.   One can spend at least 2-3 hours here.  Go early in the morning, as the colors of the orchids are most vibrant in the early morning light.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful scenery and fresh air with cafes that serve great food. The symphony garden is accentuated with a water lily pond surrounding the stage.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Really scenic & nice place for a light walk / trek; can be crowded at times but place is opened till night.

Just take note that certain paths / trails get really dark after evening.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Even on busy holidays, you can enjoy a sense of being in nature. And it's nice to be able to walk thru from Botanic Gardens to Napier train stations.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
A nice place for a jog and looking at interesting plants.
Do visit the National Orchid Garden as they orchids are really pretty and well managed.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Loved it.  This is one of the most beautiful gardens anywhere in the world. It__ clean and well cared for.  There is a lot to see and do.  The orchid garden is worth paying for.  Most of the gardens are open to the public, free of charge.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Amazing place to picnic, jog and have fresh air. Lots of plants and trees to observe, can go on a long walk around the whole place. Great place to calm your mind.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
The Singapore Botanical Garden, the first and only tropical botanic garden on the UNESCO's World Heritage list.
Within the Botanic garden there are many other garden, like the National Orchid Garden, the Jacob Ballas Children Garden, the Ginger Garden, the Eco Garden, etc...but I personally like the one "A Garden with a View. Very quiet and nice view, very relaxing...
Heritage trees some are planted since 1900, very wide variety of plants and flowers.
An amazing Orchid Garden with many different species.
A Rain Forest with nice walking path for you to stroll and view different trees and some that reach an amazing height.
You could also see squerrels running jumping around, monitor lizard roaming, birds singing and drangonflies .
A huge garden that you might need two days to cover.
Visitors with family member and children playing around and relaxing.
Good and really nice place and will be back again.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Love this garden.  So big so spacious.  Very organized but not too manicured that it lost the natural feeling.  Still feels like a tropical forest at some parts with lizards moving about freely.
The orchid garden is beautiful..._

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Large area,may spend the whole day walking and enjoying the garden.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Found many kind of trees and flowers in this garden.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A UNESCO site. A beautiful place with lots of open spaces and lots of different botany to look at. The main gate area is more interesting, which I have visited a few times. This year I tried via the Built Timah Gate and found some interesting botany too. Like all parks in Singapore, there is always wild chicken running around. There is a bamboo botany area with different types of bamboo. There is a lake called eco-lake which is small but has a pair of black swan that entertain visitors. There is also turtles and fish at the lake. We spotted lots of squirrels in this area and have a great time taking photos of them. There is birds in this area too, do look out for them. There is dragonflies and butterflies roaming around the flowers. Do visit the different gate of this gardens as they are different. So expect to spend a day just walking around the whole place and take time to enjoy the beauty of nature.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Good for visiting and relaxing and exercise

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Each time i go, i discover a new place. Need to visit more than thrice to cover all areas. Good to reach there by 4pm at least. Love the hot chocolate at the caf. Good place to relax and enjoy nature.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: An absolute stunning place to spend your worth while time here. If you are a plant and nature lover this place should sure be on your bucket list. We went as a family and we thoroughly enjoyed this place. Botanical garden is so huge and it is not a place which can be covered in 2-3 hours. You need to walk long stretched to experience each part of the garden. If you need to cover this place in one day, it is really hectic considering the tropical weather and the distance to cover. In my opinion if you really want to enjoy this place, do it in 2 to 3 days covering each sections/day. Kids have their own park with mini play areas to enjoy and spend time. Please bring umbrellas just in case, carry a fan and water bottles. Admission to this park is free. You can carry a sheet cloth to spread on the lawn and have some quality time with your family. If lucky you can enjoy a symphony concert on Saturday evenings. Getting out of the Circle Line MRT, the entrance to the park is just outside the MRT entrance.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Well maintained garden (and many smaller gardens inside). Good day for a date or family picnic. Encouraged to go Learning Garden. Orchid garden now has limited entry due to social distancing measures. Healing garden is nice, but some parts are not accessible without volunteer guides.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Well maintained botanical gardens, with many different and varied sections (natural and man-made) to encourage you to take a stroll through and discover.  There's plenty to explore with different themes for adults and children.

Nature lovers can spend the whole day here as there is seating scattered throughout, food options available, ample toilets and parts which are lively and other parts that are serene.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Best place for visitors to come to this beautiful garden, very easy to access at your own leisure time in there, not crowded and the staff and gardener are all very friendly to give you more advise on plants and flowers, you can enjoy even if you are alone there.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Very big area, good for jogging or picnic and pets and kids friendly

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: The mist house is a must visit. It's very easy to walk around in a weekday. There was no queue and it is free for Singapore residents now.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: The place is full of flora and fauna. The place conceal with huge green and diverse vegetation. People should visit this nice garden for a picnic or family get  together.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: The garden offer lots of greenery with a variety of vegetation and plants. The best part is that the garden is free to visit, for the most part, with the exception of the orchid garden which have an admission fee to enter. You might be able to catch some wildlife in this garden too, so don't be surprise. Overall it's a nice garden to walk and be outdoor

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Very beautiful gardens. It__ away from the main touristy areas so it was not very crowded. Great for a few hours of relaxing in the shade or picnicking.  There was an extra charge (I think 4-5$) for the orchid garden but considering the garden is free, why not? Overall, def worth the visit.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Fantastic. Great place to visit, lots to see  plenty of different routes to walk around. Do pay the S$5 entry for the orchid gardens as it is a special place to see all the delicate flowers we struggle to just keep alive absolutely flourishing, well worth the entrance fee. A place to see how good your photography skills really are.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: I've been here 3 years ago but did not realise there was an orchid garden with in the gardens.. must be the world's largest collection of huge different selections.. all beautiful.. well worth a visit,  and it's cool inside a break from the outside humidity.  The main gardens thems selves shows lots of green grass and interesting trees. We saw two small monitor lizards in the undergrowth.  Whole area very clean and well maintained and some good food places through.  Right next to an MRT so easy to get too.  One of the places to visit in Singapore I'm happy to recommend.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: If you're in Singapore you must visit this place. Spectacular. One of the nicest gardens I've been to. A UNESCO Heritage site. Has a fantastic collection of orchids and other local specialties. Very nice food at the central restaurant. Go early, it's very large and amazing in the morning.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Very well curated nature park, large with distinct themes at different areas. Great for exploration and definitely a place to check out!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: this place is a must visit. It has an abundance of green spaces, and a ton of different types of landscapes. There are marshes, rolling green fields, forestry and even canals, and more.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Excellant gardens, all free with many different trails, wonderful Indian , Asian, European resturant just as you enter. Breakfast choices amazing and plentiful. Staff attentive and helpful.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Even in the rain this place is a calm and tranquil wander. It__ free to enter,  signposting for direction is sporadic but just about adequate (getting lost wandering is half the fun and beauty) the National orchid garden is S$5 but worth it, the flowers are beautiful.
There__ cafes that serve food, hot drinks and alcohol.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Exceptional plant and tree diversity. The orchids were colorful, unique, and visually stunning.
We saw wild roosters and even a dragon hunting for worms.
The tree variety was immense in both size and proportions.
The paths were wide with eclectic varieties of colors to look at.
We found stunning fragrances and unique seeds, leaves, and fauna.
Sharing the time with my Singapore family created so many visual and personal loving memories
We will come back again on another day as we did not have enough time to squeeze it all in.
I paid the $5 foreigner charge was was grateful to have such a visual catalog of colors, sights, and sounds.
#RockFromRI

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Pretty place to walk around. Worth visiting

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
National Orchid Garden entrance is free until further notice.
Clean toilets and beautiful flora.
My children were excited at the sight of live chickens and chicks roaming around too.
They were in awe when theh saw the huge monitor lizards too.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Very relaxing to walk around here. Entry was for free. Beautiful maintained and remarkable flora. Time well spent here.
There many shady places to sit and contemplate about life or to listen to the nature. You can fill your water bottle close the toilet blocks, for free

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Enjoyable to walk around, though plan your route around the gardens if hot and stay out of that sun.

Good range of trees, native and non native to rainforests.

But it's the flowers you need to see. In particular the Orchid Garden. Gorgeous blooms and so many species of varying colour and size.

Would imagine throughout the year it's good to visit. We were there in October and still plenty to see.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: The park is really well maintained with varieties of plants and trees everywhere. This garden is definitely a visual treat for nature lovers.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: This was one of the highlights of our visit to Singapore. The greatest collection of orchids I've ever seen. Everything is pristine and well maintained. Highly recommended.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: It's a nice place for me. We should rest there if we got stress or anything. The plants, the view and the flower can make you get pleasure. I recommence that everyone need that kind of place.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: large park to walk around or chill in. Lots of trails and different areas, with a couple cafes and shops. In the middle is the national orchid garden which you have to pay to enter. $15 for foreigners, $5 for locals with discounts for seniors and students

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Took a joy MRT ride kiddo. End up here. Nice

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Amazing place to go for nature lovers. Explore the place to discover new facts and experience the diversity of the plant world. If lucky, you might find some birds and monitor lizards too. There are places to eat and refresh yourself. There are lakes. You could also enjoy a date at the sundial garden.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Excellent place to walk. Have a great kids section and will keep them occupied and busy. Best of all, it's free!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Beautiful garden located in central Singapore. Only one national heritage site in Singapore.
Good for walking, running, nature  photography.
Would recoomend for those who loves nature.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Best place to unwind and meditate. It__ a large garden where you can see different themes. They have a large swan lake with kiosks where you can just relax and appreciate nature. Their bonsai looks great. They even have desert theme where you can see several kinds of cacti. Flowers are well taken cared of and my special favorite is the orchidarium.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Massive! In the heat and humidity, the cafe in the middle is a true oasis. I enjoyed that a lot. The Gardens l, though, are great. Covers a huge area and as such it boasts a lot of different styles, plants and ecosystems. The rainforest makes for a nice stroll through but the beauty is in the eclectic mix of plants and flowers in various landscapes.

It__ easy to get to using public transport, which stops right outside one of the entrance gates. And it__ free. Happy days.

There are quite a few species of birds in the Gardens too, as an extra treat.

Well worth a visit.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
This is probably the most expansive botanical gardens I've ever been to. I completely underestimated how large the park is, and ended up not making it all the way to the end, despite cranking it up and just fast-walking through the park since the sun was setting. Tons of little gardens inside the park, and even a few exhibits to see like seed harvesting/preservation. Best of all, it's completely free admission, and connected to the MRT.

The end opposite the MRT has a number of restaurants and placed to sit and chill, so consider walking over and starting from that end if you're coming by subway. Definitely worth a visit if you enjoy plants and gardens. Just be prepared to do a lot of walking. The Fragrant Garden is not to be missed!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: This is singapore first UNESCO heritage site. Lushy green trees and gorgeous flowers greet you upon entering. Can consider a weekend trip down with your spouse if you are into flowers.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Expansive gardens that are well-maintained, and the majority of it is free. A peaceful place to observe nature and relax away from the crowds. The routes can be extremely long, however, so bring water and maybe even a snack. Plan carefully where you walk and end up for public transit options.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: This is one of the most delightful gardens I have ever been to! Lots of very interesting history about the plants of Singapore and wonderfully kept grounds. This place is very large but easy to walk through, with many public bathrooms and places to get food. The area is well paved and it is easy to bring a stroller. Thank  you Singapore for providing this amazing space and keeping it free and open to the public!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Absolutely beautiful gardens in the heart of Singapore. A hidden gem. Gardens are incredibly well-maintained. Staff are very friendly and informative. Would definitely recommend visiting this place if you have a few days in Singapore.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Super place, but, as northern Europeans, we found it very hot and humid. Orchid garden is excellent- it's even got a mountain environment which is deliciously cool.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: An amazing place. Peoples like me who loves green loves trees,must visit their. Thousands of trees.Nice environment. Neat and clean.Although Singapore is a very much concrete city but when you enter into this garden you will feel like you are into a jungle, a safe jungle.Thanks mother nature!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Nice garden with walking/running trails. Covered by lush trees. Great for work-outs. Many different trails and not boring.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: The Singapore Botanic Gardens is just gorgeous. It's beautiful - with many different themed areas for visitors to enjoy. It's perfect for a stroll, a picnic, a run... you can bring your yoga mat and practice on the grass or in a garden pavilion... or just relax on a bench and watch the swans in the lake. There's so much the Singapore Botanic Gardens have to offer. Even on a busy day, the gardens feel spacious. Best of all, there are no entry fees.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: The gardens are beautiful and very well looked after. Its recommended to go early in the morning as it can get very hot around 11am. A lot of different types of species to look at. Gardens are very big so carry water bottle.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: There's about five places I would recommend to visit while in Singapore. This is one of them. The Botanic Gardens are a beautiful display of what Singapore once was and yet still has kept. From start to finish this should take you over two hours if you go through all of it. Three plus hours if you really take it all in and read the display, take photos and really appreciate the marvel they have created. This has so many varieties of plant life with almost a different Eco system only meters between. There's tons of birds and wildlife at every corner and a great place to get a run in. A well maintained jungle within a city. Everything is so well maintenanced, from the walkways to even the trees. It truly is an impressive park to visit. Free to go in but certain areas cost a couple dollars to see. But worth every penny. Great place to run, exercise, meditate, people watch or just breath in the clean air and relax.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: We spent 6 hours here, and we're only able to cover 40% of the grounds. It was absolutely beautiful - you cannot miss the opportunity to go here

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: It is a good place to go to. You can learn a lot about flowers and see the different types of flowers. Would recommend going there to learn more about flowers and also go there to relax and recreate.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
I had the immense pleasure of coming here during Christmas and the amount of work/ decorations they put everywhere was astounding. On a regular day, the SBG has so many top notch attractions, you could come here for 2-3 days and be surprised with new nature beauty every time. It also looks different during the day vs. night, with its lights.

I really like the Cloud Forest and highly recommend that. Also theres a free outdoor desert plants area with a bunch of game of thrones like chairs made from branches.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Long walk, but totally worth it. Make sure you bring water to survive the humidity! If you need a break, make your way to the greenhouse, it__ much cooler!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Great green area in the city

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Nice serene surroundings. A huge garden in the city with lots of plant species, ponds, a couple of restaurants and an amazing orchid garden(but I didn't make it in__). Nice place to take a walk or lay out on the grass. It's also a popular place for joggers.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful and nice places within to stop for a meal or drink. We caught the MRT to the botanic gardens stop which pops you out right next to the gate. Its about a 1.2km walk through to the orchid area but it's easy walking. There is a closer gate if you don't like the walk but you would need to figure out the MRT closest or taxi it.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A great way to start a new year in 2020, a large national park with well maintained greenery. One can also view Singapore national flower with a garden just for them - orchids! Children or elderly will find something to do over here. A good place to visit for nature lovers.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: One of the best-reserved places in Singapore. It's very well maintained and one can spend hours roaming around or just relaxing. The place is vast and probably will take you more than half a day to fully explore it. I always enjoy going here for morning runs and then treating myself to a good full-filling breakfast in one of the many award-winning restaurants located inside the garden. Recommended full time __.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: One of the places in Singapore to visit. Should not miss the national orchid garden. Beautiful orchids some are exclusive.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: It is large, with numerous trails.  A few small informative buildings to teach about local botany, birds, & the gardens.  Make sure you visit the learning centers.  The trees and plants are mostly local.  Some are very old.  I learned about Singapore's nature.  Informative signs everywhere.  Singapore is filled with malls seemingly on every other block, but they are redundant.  Go visit Singapore's nature in this botanical gardens.  It was 94 degrees & humid outside, but it felt fine, & I'm a San Franciscan!  The air conditioning in the 3 informational museum buildings within the gardens was a nice respite from the heat & humidity I must admit though. These gardens are beautiful & educational.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Nice to take a walk in nature and we have been super lucky to experience nature !

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: It's a wonderful Garden that You can Enjoy various beautiful species of flowers.....if u are a lover of flowers and plants.... it's highly highly recommend

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful gardens in the centre of the city. We had a good time exploring all the areas. Involves a lot of walking, so go prepared! The orchid garden was the highlight. We had fun trying to identify plants in the herbs and spices garden.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: One of the best green spaces with many thematic gardens of great variety, water bodies and biodiversity. Must go if you live in Singapore or are visiting.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Very nice place, you need 5 or more hours to see most of the gardens. If you go for the Orchid Place you pay a entrance, for the Park around not, it's free.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Such an incredible haven from the busy bustle of the city. Singapore is crowned by many jewels but this must be among the grandest of them all!

The national orchid garden is 100% worth the entrance fee, some of the orchids there are almost other worldly!

This is a must visit for any tourist!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Just an amazing place. We spent almost the entire day just chilling and relaxing. The garden consists of many different sections. Ginger garden, orchid garden etc.. there is a small fee for the orchid garden but well worth the visit. It's one of the most reasonably priced attractions I have been to, and most enjoyable. The orchids are just amazing and it's a great place to get some lovely pictures. There are restaurants in site and also shops for snacks and refreshments. I would personally take a picnic if I visited next time as it's a great place to just unwind. Would reccomend taking plenty of water as there is a lot of walking to do.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Incredible park with lots to see in multiple exhibits. You need to schedule at least 4 hours if not the whole day to see this park. Most of the exhibits are free with the exception of the orchid garden, which is $5 for adults and free for children.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
One of the best Botanic Gardens I've ever been too.
It has plenty of different paths to go through, a lovely restaurant (Casa Verde) and the Orchids garden which makes everyone really happy with all the colours.
Very well taken care of and easy to get to by bus & MRT.
The kids area is also huge and great to hang out.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Amazing park! I was very excited to see the intact rainforest walk. Do yourself a favor and go see the orchard garden as well (small fee but worth every cent).
If you are a botany enthusiast, spend a whole day here. We only had a few hours and didn't even see half of the park.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Serene place for a slow, quiet and reflective walk in the cool of the evening. A good place for a slow run as well. Can see some families spreading out ground sheet for a good time of bonding in the evening.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
A wonderful and quiet place for a walk.
You won't regret to put this on your sightseeing list.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Today I went to a different part of the botanical gardens.  I didnt realise the gardens was so big. You could easily spend 4 hours if you explore the whole place..
I had been there a couple of times
But today I found out there was a Learning Forest which I didnt have time to explore.  Looking forward to doing that next trip. Love this place! Free and lots of space!!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Highly recommend for everyone to visit this botanical garden

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A good place for jogging and see all the plants. Got museum inside which is very good and educative. The garden is pretty clean with a lot of information regarding of all plants and collection. Too bad i cannot enter the poison garden without any tour.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Lovely park to stroll at, either with family, friends or even to walk the dog. Area is very well-maintained and litter-free - part of the reason I visit the place regularly every fortnight. One may pop by any of the gift shops for a small memento, and let the helpful staff there assist you. Head down to Fusion Spoon, which offers a variety of affordable casual cuisines, should a quick meal be necessary.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Good place to walk. Very large park in the city. as the heart of the city against pollution. There was an orchid garden in the center. It was Only 1 dollar to enter.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
I cannot believe this place was free.

You could spend a full day walking through this garden.  This is such a wonderful place to have in your city and something every city should have for it's residence.

The paths are long and wide and even on a Sunday afternoon it was not crowded.  Scattered throughout the gardens are also grassy parks for people to picnic and play.  Dogs are allowed in the park and they were all beautifully behaved.

All in all this was a great experience and one I would highly recommend.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: The Singapore Botanic Gardens is free to enter. The garden is absolutely beautiful and well manicured. We had a lovely relaxing day walking around. While you__e at the gardens you can visit The National Orchid Garden which is only a few dollars to enter and is well worth it. The Orchid garden is simply stunning and an orchid lovers delight. This garden is an UNESCO World Heritage garden. Wonderful place. Everyone should visit here while in Singapore. Such a huge collection of plants and trees and wildlife too.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Singapore Botanic Gardens is a place I truly love to come for a walk. It's a great place for families with young children where they can have many play areas with sand, flowers, pond, chickens, tortoises and great grass field to run around and play games.

Many also come here for yoga, ta chi, morning stretching, hike and picnic.

The garden is huge, clean and lots of small corners and areas to explore.

They hold free outdoor concerts that has amazing sound quality.

There are several cafes, restaurants and even hawker style food centre inside botanic garden.

It is a must come place for Tourists too!

The UNEACO world heritage site is filled with life! Clean and lovely air!

#ILoveSingaporeBotanicGardens

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Really lovely place to go for a walk and learn about plants and their uses. Everything is well signposted and there is information on most of the stuff you see, making it an educational walk if you want.
Regular water fountains and toilet facilities make it much more enjoyable.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: good place for walk lovers, if you not and you are in bcoz of your wife... well... get prepare for most challenging day of your life.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Tourist or local, the best garden in Singapore to visit. Now with MRT station within walking distance make it even more convenient for daily stop by stroll

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Well maintained gardens. A well kept orchid garden. An abundance of colors in orchids. Beautiful and scenic gardens. A tree is dedicated in honor of the late  President Nelson Mandela of South Africa. Easy access for tourists to the garden. Wheel chair friendly. Great for selfies and photographers.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Love the place ! Must visit in Singapore.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
They have clean restrooms, and the staff are helpful.

There's also a really nice waterfall. And a lot of spaces that are great for picnic.__

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
The place was clean and had enough signage to guard visitors. Since it is near to an MRT station, it is convenient to visit. The area is clean and one can really say that it is a garden! It has enough benches and light post to guide visitors. It is a great place to run, too.
The Shaw Symphony Stage has a great place for concert events. The uphilled area provides place for relaxed sitting positioned attendees on a clean and green grass. Since, the area was surrounded with trees, it added to a great homey and non-urban feel for concert - goers. The area is clean and spacious.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: ____Bigest double thumbs up____beautiful scenering____we can see & touch live flora & fauna____beautiful decoration of landscape____here we can get fully peace of mind very easily____beautiful sunset____heavy humans traffic during Sunday & local public holiday____fresh air & 360_ surroundings clean area____________

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful,  tranquil and free....Can't be better than that! The Orchid garden is well worth the small entrance fee. Continuous creative display throughout the whole year. If you're over 60 then it's only 1 Singapore dollar to go in.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
A very nice place to relax your mind and get engaged with nature.
Recommended to go with friends or family!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: This garden is very good amd clean. You will definitely find some peace here. Must visit once

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Great gardens loads to see

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
What an absolutely beautiful park! When in Singapore please visit this place. It is a convenient place to visit, one of the entrances of right next to the MRT stop. There are some places in the park that you have to pay for but mostly it's completely free.

If you walk from this park to the famous orchid road you will walk past the houses of the ambassadors, which is nice to see.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: True paradise, this  place is amazing. The orchid exhibit was fantastic. Unbelievably beautiful. Went on a Saturday and lucked out with the symphony playing. The grounds are so beautiful.  Well maintained and such beautiful mature trees,  really enjoyed it here. A UNESCO world heritage site.  Definitely recommend.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Very nice place. You can see lots of interesting flowers and animals. In the rainforest you can even see monkeys

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Absolutely an amazing place in the middle of hi-tech country Singapore. Here, the botanical garden is one of the UNESCO World Heritage and probably the best-mamaged garden in SE Asia. It has many important facilities for research, including the Singapore BG herbarium.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: This is a real gem. Not in main part of city but very easy to get to by MRT. just walking through the gardens is amazing. Getting the booklet is worthwhile for fascinating history and explanation of plants.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Thought I could cover everything in a day. But I was wrong. There is alot to cover which you cant cover by walking. Well maintained and helpful staffs keeps the place at it's best. If you wish to go in morning, I would recommend to carry an umbrella and a bottle of water, as it can be very hot inside. If you are person who really love to get to know about plants I would recommend this place.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Huge botanical garden and I think the most beautiful I've ever visited. Went there twice, once at night when I almost got lost on it's winding alleys but it felt very safe and it was a nice experience. The second time went there during the day and got to enjoy a good part of it before a thunderstorm started. Plenty of things to visit and the entrance is free. Recommend it

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Just stunningly beautiful!!  Such a lovely  huge garden with style. Really enjoyed the orchids especially. They are thriving and so many!!  JUST BEAUTIFUL!!

If you love orchids you must not miss it. However do take care of the heat so best to go super early to beat the sun. We went at 1:30pm and I was drenched in sweat.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Singapore Botanic gardens is on a bus route so accessis easy from the city centre.
It is a large park with tarmac paths throughout. The plants ,shrubs and trees are all well chosen and stunning specimens.
There is a lovely area for outdoor concerts and a cafe with a great menu choice.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Absolutely beautiful! These gardens were absolutely beautiful and very well set up. There is lots to see and do and bubblers for dining water. There are also lots of places to shelter if it starts to rain. There is shaded walking areas and a lot of variety to suit different tastes.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Beautiful park/gardens and very easy to get to via MRT or Grab.  The Orchid garden inside the park has an entrance fee for tourists.

Tips:
1. Bring water.  Singapore is hot and you will need to rehydrate.
2. Bring an umbrella or raincoat.  We went in December and there are random heavy rains.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Nice gardens and exhibitions, clean and peaceful environment and many good cafes nearby. The national orchid garden is always my favourite place. It is also a nice walk from Bukit Timah gate to Orchard road.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: It's a nice big place for plant lovers. The park size is huge. Having a map of the place is a must or else one might get lost inside. Plants with different themes have been put at different places. There is a lake in between and also a stage for concerts.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A great garden to spend  cool morning wondering around. The garden is very well maintained and the walk around is quite easy when it__ not too hot. Lots of shaded areas to rest and plenty to see. Easily accessible using the MRT station conveniently located at one of the entrances

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Wonderful park with a lot of Nature, different kind of flowers, trees, Animals walking around.. i didn't find mosquitos so It was so good! You can bring food and have a picnic or eat at the restaurants inside. Perfect for a long walk in the nature, relax, jogging, enjoy the peaceful.. very recommended

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Great park to exercise and walk.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful. A must visit when in Singapore.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Absolutely worth a visit. This beautiful and admirable garden with cozy paths, wildlife animals, kids area and informative notes of the greenery - so it is at the UNESCO world heritage list.
Don't miss it out if you like nature parks. Do bring a picnic or so and sit by the lake and look at the black swans and other birds.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Always a fun outing for families and nature lovers. It's a popular destination with locals and tourists so could see quite a lot of people sometimes. Evening strolls or picnics are perfect. It's a big place, a day won't be enough for tourists who are into plants and habitats, many information to read and photos to take!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: 1st visit and it was fantastic.  I may be biased but grass was clean and soft and felt different to the touch.  Now i know why its so visited.  Perfect for families to hangout, greenery lovers, tree hugers.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Amazing place. One day not enough to enjoy fully. So big and every small piece maintained very well. The must visit place in Singapore and you will not regret for visiting.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Walking through the park was so nice and clam, good information points and maps.  Food restaurantsl available. There are so many different types of trees, flowers and plants to see.  Lots of spaces to run away, don't forget to take bottle of water.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Soothing! This place is a treat for the eyes. Well maintained Flora spread over acres. It's just what you need when you want to relax and spend time with your loved ones. It's a perfect picnic spot and also doubles up as a spot for photoshoots. The variety of flora available here is extensive. They have descriptions on them and is quite informative. However it's a long walk and it can get exhausting. Seating is available however not so many. It's metres away from the nearest metro station. Again, wonderful place for a visit to get out of the hustle and bustle of the city.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: It was a great place to spend the early afternoon. Got to hot later in the afternoon. We could have spent a lot more time walking around. Also very convenient with the transit station. Would definitely recommend.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Proud of our own gardens, it is one of the first UNESCO Heritage. A must visit if you are in Singapore. There are activities for the old, young, pets and humans.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Definitely worth visit when you're in Singapore. The flowers and trees are beautiful. The on site cafe serves very good fresh food. There is a very interesting Ethnobotany Centre in the grounds.  The orchid garden is fantastic! There are small turtles swimming in the lake.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful park in the center of the city, with several attractions, restaurants and gift shops. Great place to picnic, play sports, listen to a concert or just enjoy a long walk surrounded by flowers and tropical rainforest. Next to the MRT station, can't miss it!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful! Such a wonderful garden and FREE! Spent 4 hours there and felt like I could have stayed longer. While roaming all the different sections you__l fine heaps of interesting facts about the plants. One of my favorite sections was the reflexology path, the sun shines in the area well heating the stones. Take off your shoes and walking across the path.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A beautiful botanical garden with so many fine examples of flowers from the region. The garden's are well laid out and cared for and it was an absolute delight to see them. The Ginger and Orchid gardens are particularly beautiful. Free too  except a small charge for the Orchid Gardens  - but well worth it  !

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful part of Singapore to visit if you are  into nature and flowers! There are so many pathways it is not likely you will be able to travel all of them in one day. There are multiple entrances into the park and everything is free except the orchid garden which is $5. Plan for several hours and bring lots of water. There are drinking fountains throughout the park as well to refill but the water is not cold.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A must see botanic garden in Singapore. Spectacular garden plants and flowers in a peaceful quite setting. Take a few hours out of your day while visiting Singapore  and stroll along the garden paths. The orchid flowers are amazing!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Founded in 1859, the Singapore Botanic Gardens showcases the best and most spectacular of tropical flora set in stunning verdant landscape.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Not bad of a visit if you enjoy the sight of Orchids. Some portions were under construction when I visited hence that area was closed. Entrance fee was SGD 5 but I'm not sure due to what reason it is temporarily free till further notice.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A must see for anyone visiting Singapore.  There is no entry fee. A very big garden right on exit of the mrt station. There is a large pond in between and lots of playgrounds with slides and children play areas. Make sure to get some sand play toys if you have toddlers. One can easily spend an entire day here.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Enjoyed my day strolling around the beautiful gardens. Would definitely recommend going when the weather is nice and sunny!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Great place to relax on weekends. Visiting before 11 am and after 4 pm will be good weather, otherwise it will be very hot just imagine snowman in summer __ except  on cloudy days. These pictures area is close to MRT station. There's a lake, we can see some animals live there such as swans, turtles, birds, chickens, and also has children's garden. Many group of people like to spend their weekends and sit around this park

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Singapore botanical garden

A botanical garden registered with UNESCO in Singapore.  You can go around while watching many plants.  However, because it is a very large land, if you do not decide where to go in the botanical garden, it will be boring just walking.  For photographers, there are many subjects.  But unfortunately I don't recommend it to those who take videos.

*

There is a university in this botanical garden, so you can have school meals here at noon.  Since it is a very international university, I saw people of various nationalities.  I thought it was Singapore.

*

Probably walked for about 3 hours.  Finally, a big otter was taking a nap so I took a picture.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Amazing gardens! Amazing that most of it is free. So many beautiful flowers, trees, bushes, and water features. If you go during a weekday it__ not even crowded.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: If you're experiencing stress and anxiety, consider connecting with nature as it can have a healing effect. Here's a great option to do so.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Always my favourite place to get in some quiet me time (if you know where to avoid the large group excercise/dance spots - you will probably hear loud blasting music and screaming fit instructors anyway). One of the best kept public gardens I've seen around the world.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful, tranquil place amidst hustle of the city. Very good for kids. Perfect place to spend your morning roaming around and enjoying the nature with kids and family.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
This beautiful a d amazing garden,  has been inscribed as a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 2015. The Gardens is the first and only tropical botanic garden on the UNESCO__ World Heritage List.
A beautiful place to visit, I recommend it.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: This has to be one of the best botanical gardens I have visited. It is such a pleasure to just wander round and see all the various different plants on show. The Orchid garden in the centre is well worth paying to enter and see.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful natural garden, with an array of plants full of color, tall trees, river walk, trails, and rest stops. Be mindful of the local wildlife there.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Great place for all ages.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Great place for  viewing some stunning botanical gardens. Due to the local climate, everything is beautiful and green. The garden is quite large, so you could spend several hours wandering around here. The National orchid garden was really nice as well. I'd probably recommend going in a cooler part of the day to avoid most of the heat

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Really beautiful plants and great to have an early morning long stroll before it gets really crowded! Never missed the orchid garden and do expect to get sweaty (rmb your sunscreen) with singapore's humid weather.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Little disappointing as a non-botanist, there could be more education materials there, and indications for what plants are present.

In the end it felt like a particularly nice park.

That bring said, access is free and it is very nice so i would definitely recommend.

The orchid garden within is also excellent, and reasonably priced at $5. I would definitely recommend that one as well.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful gardens with the most magnificent plants and plenty of shade while walking around and it__ all very close to the city. We caught the hop on hop off bus and did the Botanical Gardens it was a great day. Some Nice eatery__ there as well.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Amazing place to be in anytime (as long as the weather is good) full of green colour and superb scenery. Lakes are amazing with white swans and fishes.
Very old trees from different parts of the world with a lot of variety. It's very useful to ask the info people as they are so much supportive and cooperative with passion. Don't forget to pass by the Singaporean traditional tree Tembasu and take a picture with $5.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: This trip, started from the Tyersall gate visiting the learning forest, SPH Walks of Giant and Keppel Discovery Wetlands. Wonderful places, overlook a huge pond on the bridge. Plenty of monitor lizards, on the tree trunk or on the ground digging the soil looking for worms. Also walked over to the nearby Orchard Plaza which is free of charge now

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: It has several gates. It's a very large garden with a lot of cozy garden area. It has visitor center with a kind of rest area. Free admission! I love being here. Sure will come back here again with my children someday. I wonder how singaporeans take care of this huge garden. I wonder how they manage it, so clean and enjoyable.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: It was really nice. I sat down and had a picnic with my friends and I, and we had a lot of fun. As long as you choose a good spot near some trees, and possibly a gazebo just in case it rains, the view and the place is really nice! I recommend coming here for walks around the park.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Big beauitful garden with a lot of special trees.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Wonderfully maintained grounds.
We went early spring as flowers are just blooming.
Lots of orchid displays but you have to be lucky to see them.
You must try a ginger muffin & a coffee in the Ginger Garden cafe! Very different but delicious!
Swans & otters on the Swan Lake provide fauna amongst the flora.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: What a tranquil and beautiful place to be at. Mornings are peaceful , esp.weekdays. Weekends can be too busy.  Evenings are good and Shaw Foundation Symphony area holds some good concerts or shows from.time to.time, very good for a little picnic.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Try to spend 1 complete day atleast. Keep a bottle of water and go if you are nature lover. You will love this place if you like to walk and enjoy garden. I loved this place completely.

It was clean and was properly managed. There were maps everywhere and you can spot some monitor lizards, reptiles, rabbits, birds and a few more animals. The walk was amazing inside the bamboos and other parts. Must visit.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Singapore's first unesco heritage site. Well maintained, Natural and entertaining with many things to do in a relatively small place (not small by absolute terms, but compared to other big places where one need to go around to cover such things). Easily accessible with multiple entry points and good food places to refill when exhausted. Liked the rainy forest and lakes in between. Time well spent on a weekend and would probably go again as many spots were not covered during the first visit

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Nice place to meet unspoiled and non-artificial Singapore Nature. One can spent several hours in this nice garden, and of course - the adjacent Orchid Garden. Everything is well - maintained, kept, designed. There are most of all asphalt tracks,but also some wooden pathways through the "city jungle". In march 2018 no mosquitoes, so no need to take precautions. There are some ponds, or even lakes, with swans and other fowl, and some wandering cocks in the "jungle". Different trees from different parts of the world, arranged in groups and thematically.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: UNESCO site in Singapore. Quite a huge garden to walk about. Have swans and terrapins and cocks, as well as dragonflies and iguanas. Squirrels at some areas. Bring insect repellent to apply. Great place for macro shooters bird shooters, as well as for jogging or just for walks! There's orchid garden but need to pay to enter. But its worth the price!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
These botanical gardens are a jewel.

They__e huge, there are a ton of different areas, and everything is well-laid out, well-signed, and set up for both active learning and peaceful enjoyment, or anything in between.

The free entry is a nice touch.

The National Orchid Garden is an exception, but it__ worth the S$15 tourist price.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: One of my favorite place in Singapore to take a walk and enjoy festivities from food bazaar to symphony in the park.  Loved it and hope it can stay clean, well-maintained and green as it is meant to be in the heart of he city.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Loved visiting the Singapore Botanic Gardens. Make sure you visit the National Orchid Garden as well (100% worth the admission cost).

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: One of the best in the world I've seen with it's outstanding orchids orchard. You can run or walk or rest in a safe and perfectly maintained place. Kind people anywhere offering their help if you miss the right way.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Love the greens and their scenery! First time I went to Flower dome and I already in love with the place! Because I love plants and as an Illustrator, I've got so much references, thanks to Flower Dome!__

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Absolutely beautiful garden with some many different exotic orchids and other beautiful sights. Don't forget to bring your hat, water, comfy shoes and always a good camera. Because you can have one of the coolest IG photos in here.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Fantastic community space. the Orchid gardens are well priced and all the spaces with plaques and Wayfinding made it a very fluid and informative experience.

One of the nicest Botanic Gardens I've been to. In fact the Orchid gardens was such an experience that I'm going to try plant orchids of my own!

Will come back, need at least a full day here so you can take your time

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Gorgeous and quiet gardens, it's free but you can make a donation online. Very peaceful and made for a perfect walk on a hot summers day.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Fabulous gardens. Orchids especially were exquisite.  Needed to spend more time there but we were on a coach trip.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Beautiful nice place!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
There's no entrance fee (just for the orchids gardens). It's absolutely beautiful. There was a storm when we were there and that made the experience even better.

Make sure you take a bottle of water with you.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Really enjoyed a half day walking around here_ it__ immaculately kept and lots of helpful staff if you have questions.
The Orchid house (extra charge) is a must especially the high altitude room_
Lots of places to eat and drink _ I had a Singapore Sling to go and it was delicious.
There is no paper map or WiFi so download before you visit if you don__ have phone service.
Easy to get to by Metro and bus service, I took Metro from Chinatown, walked the length of park North to South then caught a bus to my hotel on Orchard Road.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: This place is nice for walks, relaxation and hangout with friends or family. It consists of several gardens here, which is recognized as a world heritage site. Some people also do suntan here. Bicycle is not allowed in the gardens but it's possible to park nearby the entrance. Bring some water as the heat will makes you thirsty.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: It's really clean and green area. I got nice feeling when i was there. Peaceful feeling guys don't miss out. Thank you National Environmental Agency and ____ Singapore. I would like to visit again during rainy days to feel it.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: The main part of the Botanic Gardens is free access, only for the Orchid Garden there is a small entrance fee, which is only 1$ for students. The Gardens themselves are nice to walk in, and the Orchid Garden is beautiful. I would recommend 2 hours for this place. It is definitely worth a visit.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Suitable for a morning or evening casual walk. There are also many cafe choices for brunch within the park. More popular ones would be Bees Knees and Casa Verde. Lastly, I would highly recommend to bring along mosquito repellent.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: The Botanic Gardens is a group of sprawling peaceful and well-planned gardens, rich in flora and foliage, wildlife, makes you feel relaxed and happy, whether alone or with others. At Jacob Ballas Children's Garden alone, I saw a great diversity of animals at different spots, I saw a baby kingfisher dive several times for food at a pond, three waterhens, a black swan preen its feathers and swim about, three water monitor lizards at various spots, many turtles, two squirrels, four species of butterflies and other types of birds all within two hours. Exciting and fulfilling! Especially for photo buffs!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Like anything in Singapore the gardens are well planned. The gardens are very big and you can spend there 5 hours. However, we were there approximately two hours, visited the west side of the park.
Variety of plants, trees, flowers and animals (in the lake).
Some of the activities inside the gardens require entry fees while the entry to the botanic gardens is free of cost.
We had great experience there and I wish you too.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Absolutely beautiful park in the middle of the hustle and bustle of one of the most vibrant cities in the world. If you visit, pay for admission to the orchid garden. Truly a site to see.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Botanical gardens...very big park and so nice the fresh air,more flowers,fishes,flamingo swan and small water falls river and many mores there....can go picknick also there and bingy jumping and can walk to hiking trill...

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: One of the good place to visit. You can enjoy the beauty of the nature. Well maintained place. Bring your kids and enjoy. Kids will love this place.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Huge and great gardens. Will probably take you 3 hrs. to cover all the areas. It is free, except for the orchid center where the charges is $5/pax (foreigners only). Don't miss it.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: It is a very large park with various collection of plants, such as orchids, cacti, fragrant flowers, and bougainvillea. With many open green spaces, people can go for a picnic with family or friends here on a nice day. It is also a good place for jogging. It is free to enter these gardens, but there are no free drinking water taps. However, there are several cafes here.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: We went a few places to clock our miles on a beautiful weekend. Mingxia foundation ramblers bridge, the botanical art gallery at Gallop Extension and Keppel discovery wetlands. __

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: One of the most beautiful gardens I ever saw. Many theme based gardens inside this park adds to the charm of the place

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Wonderful very well-curated gardens.
UNESCO heritage site.
Metro station __otanic Gardens_ just by the entrance.
Free admission (except the Orchid garden).
Visitor centers with WCs, souvenir shops, cafes  and drink machines.
Logical pathways and plenty of signs where to proceed.
Very vast territory, green and with exotic flower scents.
Interesting and educational experience.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A Heaven for photographers...Awesome place with variety of plants specially Orchid garden is one of the  must visit place here (Entry fee 5 SGD). if you need to explore everything minimum 5 to 6 hours are required, better to follow the route map here (you will get it on the entrance). Locker facility is also available.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Every day is a different experience at this beautiful Garden. __

Weekends are usually too crowded.. seems like a place that people like to go to, to spend family time. That includes maids working in Singapore who likes to go there for picnics.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Quite big, integrated with MRT Station, quite enjoyed walking around in Saturday noon. Seeing many families had picnics here, many others just walking or jogging. It has a lake in the middle with some turtles in it, a garden cafe and I saw a big lizzard crossed our path. Oh my!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
It is simply nice for a small family tour or picnic. The lawns there are big enough for everyone to sit on, for the kids to run randomly without getting hurt (no serious blocks except the palm trees).
One tip is there are many gates, the mrt one is like 900m away from the taxi or other car park one.
So, if you really decide to go, ready for all the walk lah.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Large garden that is slightly hilly which includes the national orchid garden. The garden is free to enter but costs 5 sing to enter the orchid garden. If you care a local, I would wait until next year as a good section of this is currently under improvements

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Nature therapy at its best!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: One of the best garden in Singapore which you should visit.  The garden is full of amazing trees, plants and wildlife.  A good place for family outing and exercise.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Relaxing place to spend the day. Beautiful walks, amazing trees, plants and flowers.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Amazing place, like to visit again and again, its really quiet nice in the evenings too! Highly recommend

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: What's not to love about Botanical Gardens? Tranquil, lush and perfect place for almost anything from exercise to chilling with family & friends

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Best best best ________

Not to be confused with the_Gardens on the Bay, the Botanic Gardens are also worth a visit. Singapore received its first UNESCO World Heritage nomination for the botanic gardens, and with good reason. The city can sometimes feel like a concrete jungle, albeit a clean and comfortable one, but the botanic gardens preserve pieces of Singapore's wilder heritage. Indeed, a walking trail leads to the gardens' heritage trees, which are conserved as part of an effort to protect the city's mature tree species. Make sure to see the impressive_National Orchid Garden. Other popular things to do include visiting the eco-garden, eco-lake, bonsai garden, sculptures, and several other gardens and unique sites.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A good place for nature walk and to enjoy the variety of trees and flowers.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A must visit place with kids and family. It__ so green and refreshing.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: What a park! Lots of plants are seen their. The attracted things are their that the plants are maintain properly and classified them based on their medicinal properties.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: a great place to hang out for picnic or so...pretty nice if can sit on the lawning in front the heritage bungalow that was built for a British lawyer in early 20th century

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: It was a relaxing and enjoyable experience with so many beautiful colourful flowers and trees surrounded in Singapore Botanical Garden. A great place to chill out with family loved ones and friends for gathering.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Amazing park. Everything is beautiful, understandable why it is under UNESCO World Heritage.
Go, visit, have some rest, take your time _________

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Breathtaking!! This place is truly heaven on Earth and a sign of the Singapore peoples_ love and appreciation of nature. A must see place for everyone visiting Singapore.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: It is a beautiful garden, it has so many tries which give u a cool environment.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Always worth spending a few hours to stroll through Botanic Gardens. This time, we saw the Singapore Garden Festival and it had gorgeous installations.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: The only Botanical Garden in Asia that was conserved as the Heritage Site. A place one should not miss when visiting Singapore. It has the best tropical garden and the well developed Orchard Garden. It also has many wild lives that roam the garden; it is well known for the Malayan Monitor Lizard, the clouded Monitor lizard, the Changing Lizard, the squirrels, the eagle feeding on the cat fish. Of course many amazing plants too.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
December celebrating POINSETTIA WISHES at Gardens by the Bay. All set up with Christmas decorations with Floral & Fauna to jingle in the Christmas Mood. Today ITE West students and teachers chaperone seniors from Bukit Timah to share the afternoon together. Heart Warming Smiles and Gentle Care we stroll together amid beautiful, fairyland like atmosphere, very cool indeed.

The Staff their were helpful and accommodating, a feather for their cap. Do bring your best camera, mobile cam, WeFi sticks, family & friends for a vibrant and colourful photoshoots. You must visit FLOWER DOME & CLOUD FOREST and outdoor gardens to add to your photo album. Visitors, regardless of their nationalities will be very happy to help shoot your groupies photos.

This is my 3rd visit to Gardens by the Bay and everytime they have different decorations with seasonal flowers on display. It'll be hard to spot a wilted flower on display because they work very hard to replace the plants in an indoor environment.

If you are planning to visit Singapore, do keep Gardens  by the Bay on your schedules. Yes, in the evening after 7.00pm, the whole place lit up and you are in another spectrum with colourful displays enhanced by carefully placed lighting. Come experience for yourself, voted Top 10 Garden and Conservatory in the World. Enjoy!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Recommended for anyone who loves lush greenery. There is an MRT station and bus stop next to one of the gates. Admission is free except for the orchid garden. Most of the park is accessible to people with mobility issues but there are some stairs here and there though there is also usually an alternative path to avoid them.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
For such a large city, you'll be shocked at the amount of parks that share space with the skyscrapers. And the Singapore Botanic Gardens is the epicenter of this natural, flowering splendor. Formerly an unused plantation, the garden hugs 60 acres of the city, not only living up to Singapore's nickname of the City in the Garden, but earning the country's first UNESCO World Heritage site title. The gardens attract both casual naturalists and scholarly botanists with its world-renowned botanical library, acres of varied vegetation and free admission. Numerous attractions dot a map of the gardens; however, we advise that you simply wander through this gorgeous spectacle and unwind. That said: travelers say not to miss the National Orchid Garden for its innumerable floral varieties and breathtaking colors.

Overall, recent visitors were taken by the beauty of the floral grounds, with some saying it was the best attraction they visited during their time in Singapore. Due to the size of the gardens, many travelers suggested allotting hours to tour this attraction because there is just that much to see. Aside from hitting the main points of interests, some recommended taking a jog or packing a picnic as an alternative means of soaking up the attraction. However you decide to experience the gardens, travelers agreed: bring water. With average temperatures reaching the 80s, it's essential you have a bottle to stay hydrated.

The Singapore Botanic Gardens are open daily from 5 a.m. to midnight and cost nothing to explore. However, the National Orchid Garden _ the park's crown jewel _ only welcomes visitors from 8:30 a.m. to 7 p.m. and charges SG$5 (about $3.75) for adult admission. Students and seniors receive reduced SG$1 (about $0.75) tickets. You can reach the Singapore Botanic Gardens by getting off at the Orchard or Botanic Gardens MRT stops. For more information check out the Singapore Botanic Garden's website.

The gardens are incredibly well tended and designed (a world heritage site). Information is posted throughout the gardens telling you about the specimens and the history of the gardens. Whisk 1 1/2 cups flour, 3 tablespoons sugar, 1 1/2 teaspoons baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon baking soda in a medium bowl.

Whisk 1 cup plus 2 tablespoons milk, 4 tablespoons melted butter and 1 egg in a separate bowl; fold into the flour mixture until just combined (it's OK if there are some lumps).

Brush a large nonstick skillet or griddle with butter and heat over medium-low heat. Add  cupfuls of batter and cook until bubbly on top and golden on the bottom, about 4 minutes. Flip and cook until golden on the bottom, about 2 more minutes. (Makes 6 to 8 pancakes.)

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: A very lovely historic park, since 1859. Nice and clean and very well looked after. Some wildlife to be seen, some rare plants too. Very large park with great paths. 1 area was closed for maintenance, which was the Jacob Ballas Children's Area. Still good to look around from MRT entrance to Holland Road (Tanglin Gate).

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: What a wonderful lashing green place I never have been seen before. Great place to visit in Singapore.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Amazing place for plant and flower lovers..

The National Orchid Garden, located within the Singapore Botanic Gardens, was opened on 20 October 1995. You can find different varieties of orchids here, even some that are devoted to celebrities.

Colourful garden with amazing flower smell surroundings. Highly recommended..

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
One of the highlights of any trip to Singapore and a must visit attraction. There is a lot to see, and after three 2-3 hour visits I think I've done most of it now.

If you're in Singapore for a while, do the whole thing. If you've only got one day set aside for the Botanic gardens, I'd suggest entering from Tanglin Gate and walking from the entrance to Swan Lake, Learning Forest, Ginger, Orchid (amazing) then round the other lake in Palm Valley (I think) towards Nassim Gate, back round the lake through the rainforest, bonsai trees then out again!

The north side of the gardens is great too, plenty more to see and definitely worth a visit, though if you only have one day it really is worth seeing the Orchids and that's best accessed from Tanglin Gate, not Botanic Gardens MRT.

Though its a bit boring, the gardens is extremely well set up for visitors, with plenty of toilets, eateries, vending machines and bins. There are plenty of places to rest, which is great as it will get hot.

Love it here!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Whether for nature lovers or not, it is a must visit garden for the young and old. A World Heritage site with a rich heritage history and collections of wonderful plants and trees.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Various different trees. Great for run or walk. The orchid garden inside the botanic garden has a entrance fee but full of amazing variety of orchids. Especially during Chinese New Year and National Day you can spot amazing flora!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Spend an hour or two exploring the garden or spend half of your day here---wouldn't be a waste. Good way to escape the hustle and bustle of the city and just recollect your thoughts__

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Botanic Gardens is the best natural gateway in Singapore. They have nurtured and developed various types of forests in there. The places is spread over 82 hectares and has been honoured as a UNESCO world heritage site. The garden is open from 5am to 12am every day and has no entry fees. There are a number of attractions within the garden, they include : Burkill Hall, Orchid Garden, Orchidarium, Tan Hoon Siang Misthouse, Coolhouse, Rainforest, Ginger Garden, Botany Centre, Jacob Ballas Children's Garden and others. Botanic Garden has three lakes, namely Symphony Lake, Eco-Lake and Swan Lake. The garden demonstrates a world class and modern botanic garden, scientific institution and place of conservation and education.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens

Toilets and restaurants are available, too. A MRT station is located right at the entrance. The orchid garden is very beautiful and (for 5SGD) definitely worth it. All other parts of the garden can be accessed for free.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Get away from the hustle & bustle of Singapore with a wander around this vast botanic garden, one of only a few to be recognised as a UNESCO world heritage site.  Within the grounds a various areas showcasing plants from different ecosystems and uses, e.g. there is a section for plants with medicinal properties that are organised by the parts of the body they affect.  There are also separate sub-parks: the orchid garden (ticket required), a section of rainforest, the ginger garden and a childrens garden (separate entrance from the road).  It can't get pretty humid here, possibly more so than the city but the tranquility is worth it.  There are lots of shelters along the walking paths to escape the downpours that often occur.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: The Singapore Botanic Gardens is a national landmark and features a small tropical rainforest, a ginger garden and an orchid garden. The tropical rainforest is one of among the only few pieces of original jungle left on the island and it__ reported to have more than 300 species of flora. The tallest trees stand about 40 metres in height. This picturesque spot is not only a perfect location to view exotic plants, trees and flowers but also all kinds of colourful birds and insects. Among them are oriental pied hornbills, spotted wood owls, crimson sunbirds and stork billed kingfishers, thanks to the ponds and lakes which attract the birds to the area. Some geese, black swans and ducks have made the gardens their permanent home, too.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Convieniently accesible via cars, bus or mrt. Immerse completely in nature. You will get to see flora and fauna. Alot of biodiversity around ranging from bird species to squirrels to turtles etc.

Good place for the family and kids. Alot of people walking their dogs or jogging. There is also an amphitheatre/ stage area near the water. Very relaxing place.

Good to visit in the evening and early morning when it is less sunny.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Do not miss it while visiting Singapore.

Highly recommend

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Foliage lined paths take you from city's edge to forest center and beyond. Deep shadows, brilliant sunlight and sparkling waters await your discovery here. Oh. And about a kajillion plants from all over the world!
Bukit Timah gate is across from the Blue Line DT 9 MRT station and offers flowering shrubs with flitting butterflies,  tranquil walks through bamboo forests and beside pretty ponds as you make your way toward the Tanglin gate and orchid garden area. You may see monitor lizards scratching up lunch beneath crunchy fallen leaves. You may encounter a family of jungle fowl, proud papa rooster hollering as he watches mama and her pullets. Look for suncatcher birds, bulbuls and more. Near water features are scarlet flitting insects (dragonflies and damsel flies, harmless). There are benches, gazebos and grassy lawns to rest a spell or have a picnic. There are only a few restaurants to grab food or a beverage, though, so bring your own refreshments in order to stay cheerful in this heat. A sunhat, umbrella and bug repellent are also good ideas. If you long for a cool moment there is a small museum open weekdays or the gift shops. Main tip: choose one gate that is close to what you'd most like to see (The Learning Forest, Orchid Garden, Children's Garden, Palm Tree area, etc.) and go see that first. Then if you have time and energy, go see more.
There are busses across the road from the Tanglin gate at the Gleneagles Hospital so you can always go home that way if you don't want to walk all the way back to Bukit Timah and the MRT station if that's where you started. Look for friendly security staff at the gates who can help direct you.
Most of all, marvel at the diversity of this world heritage site!

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
A really beautiful gardens to walk around. Easily accessible via public transport - there is a train station right next to it, the gardens are a beautiful collection of gardens, lawns and lakes. The otters in one of the lakes amused us greatly!
A must visit is the orchid house; the small extra cost is certainly worth it.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text:
Situated just five minutes away from bustling Orchard Road, the Singapore Botanic Gardens is a lush sanctuary in the heart of the city.

The Gardens has been developed along a Four-Core Concept. The four cores are Tanglin, which is the heritage core retaining the old favourites and charms of the historic Gardens; Central is the tourist belt of the Gardens; and Bukit Timah the educational and discovery zone. A fourth core, Tyersall-Gallop, was created with the opening in 2017 of the Learning Forest which is designed to integrate with the Gardens' existing rain forest to form an enlarged forest habitat.

Each Core presents an exciting array of attractions. Take your time to stroll around the Gardens and enjoy the wonderful sights and sounds the luscious greenery offers.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: The Botanic Gardens is a great place for relaxation and exercise. The Gardens are open from 5am to midnight daily. In addition, they have fantastic programmes  for visiting families and tourists every month. Do not miss the very educational and interesting guided tours on Orchid growing as well as on the history of the Botanic Gardens as a UNESCO heritage site. The Gardens has been responsible for the development of cash crops such as rubber planting for many Southeast Asian countries in the 19th and 20th centuries. The best time to visit the Gardens is the early morning before the heat of the midday sun becomes too intense.

name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
review_text: Wonderful park to spend a morning, an afternoon, an evening... plenty of trail paths if you want to run or just take a stroll. Different attractions, including a Bonsai display, if you are a lover! The trail through the patch of rainforest is a backside flip to the past! It is really relaxing!
